&lt;p&gt;I wrote a little essay for &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.smashingmagazine.com/printed-books/smashing-magazine-print-1/&#34;&gt;Smashing Print #1: Ethics &amp;amp; Privacy&lt;/a&gt; titled ‚ÄòThis One Weird Trick Tells Us Everything About You.‚Äô&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It covers different types of tracking and how it came to exist, as well as regulation, ethics, and why we need better business models. It was very cathartic to write, and I was grateful for the editorial input of the ever-thoughtful &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.fullcreammilk.co.uk&#34;&gt;Owen Gregory&lt;/a&gt;. Also I‚Äôm well pleased to have my thoughts alongside an essay by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.trinefalbe.com&#34;&gt;Trine Falbe&lt;/a&gt; and the writing of &lt;a href=&#34;https://webdevlaw.uk&#34;&gt;Heather Burns&lt;/a&gt;, people whose work I massively admire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.smashingmagazine.com/printed-books/smashing-magazine-print-1/&#34;&gt;You can get the magazine in print or as an ebook over on the Smashing Magazine site&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;



