&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúSo, what does privacy have to do with this? This question calls for another question: whose privacy are we fighting for when we say we defend the right to privacy? Talking about privacy in the abstract ‚Äì as if we all benefit from the same rights, as if we are all equal ‚Äì means taking the risk of defending the rights of only the most privileged ones in society ‚Äì with privilege coming in different forms from having a voice to be heard to socio-economic status.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
