    /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;performance&#34;&gt;Performance!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nowadays performance seems to be the hot topic of the web industry. So let‚Äôs have a look at how we might improve the speed of a web page.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;figure&gt;


    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/006_hua7a82b7ab3c199a5d03fc2f0c814946c_472240_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/006_hua7a82b7ab3c199a5d03fc2f0c814946c_472240_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/006_hua7a82b7ab3c199a5d03fc2f0c814946c_472240_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/006_hua7a82b7ab3c199a5d03fc2f0c814946c_472240_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/006.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;006.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Screenshot of the Onion homepage&#39;
    /&gt;

    &lt;figcaption&gt;


      &lt;p&gt;theonion.com&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theonion.com&#34;&gt;the Onion homepage&lt;/a&gt;, you can see it‚Äôs loading lots of images and a few videos. It‚Äôs mostly images and text content. There‚Äôs a big sticky ad at the bottom of the viewport that takes a while to load.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/009_hud15a67af7b9f93e594cb0d1187e74d0a_314827_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/009_hud15a67af7b9f93e594cb0d1187e74d0a_314827_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/009_hud15a67af7b9f93e594cb0d1187e74d0a_314827_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/009_hud15a67af7b9f93e594cb0d1187e74d0a_314827_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/009.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;009.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Safari Web Inspector for The Onion: 384 resources, 8MB, 15.24 seconds, 205 errors, 8 warnings&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you look at what‚Äôs loading behind the scenes, you can see a the layout being rendered, loading in all the content first, then more and more requests as new stuff is being loaded in. All in all, they‚Äôre loading 384 resources, coming in at 8MB, taking 15.24 seconds minimum to load. (There‚Äôs also 205 errors which may well be impacting that load time.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If we look at Safari‚Äôs Network Requests tab, we can see a little more of what‚Äôs being loaded in. If we look at the requests by size:&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/011_huf1134a225ab23e937aa6943740a49d82_644096_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/011_huf1134a225ab23e937aa6943740a49d82_644096_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/011_huf1134a225ab23e937aa6943740a49d82_644096_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/011_huf1134a225ab23e937aa6943740a49d82_644096_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/011.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;011.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Screenshot of Safari web inspector‚Äôs resources. Showing the files listed below&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.html&lt;/strong&gt; the primary HTML document is only the 19th largest file being loaded&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The largest file is &lt;strong&gt;.js&lt;/strong&gt;, a biggish javascript file, that‚Äôs fairly standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The next &lt;strong&gt;.js&lt;/strong&gt; file is a lightbox script, there‚Äôs an external &lt;abbr title=&#34;Content Delivery Network&#34;&gt;CDN&lt;/abbr&gt; for fast loading, that‚Äôs fine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.css&lt;/strong&gt; is CSS, which is very important!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.js&lt;/strong&gt; is jQuery, fine if you must‚Ä¶&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.jpg&lt;/strong&gt; is a big picture of houses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But then there is also‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;addthis.com&lt;/strong&gt; AddThis social buttons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;addthis.com&lt;/strong&gt; more AddThis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;perfectmarket.com&lt;/strong&gt; Perfect Market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;taboola.com&lt;/strong&gt; Taboola&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;taboola.com&lt;/strong&gt; Taboola again&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;doubleclick.net&lt;/strong&gt; Google DoubleClick&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;krxd.net&lt;/strong&gt; Krux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;moatads.com&lt;/strong&gt; Moat Ads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;googlesyndication.com&lt;/strong&gt; Google Syndication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;googlesyndication.com&lt;/strong&gt; Google Syndication again&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;optimizely.com&lt;/strong&gt; Optimizely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;googleadservices.com&lt;/strong&gt; Google Ad Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2mdn.net&lt;/strong&gt; which I know is another domain for Google DoubleClick.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I could go on for other 408 requests but I‚Äôd be here for a week. These are all scripts for tracking people in one way or another.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What would happen if we just load the main page without any third party tracking scripts? Let‚Äôs look again at that timeline, but this time with those third party tracking scripts blocked:&lt;/p&gt;



