&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúBut you don‚Äôt have to be on Facebook!‚Äù We hear this all the time from people who have never joined Facebook, have no intention of leaving Facebook, who don‚Äôt socialise, or who are generally pedantic and tedious. My answer is: NOPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;you-cant-just-leave-facebook&#34;&gt;You can‚Äôt just leave Facebook&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can‚Äôt just leave Facebook. First of all, you‚Äôd end up severing social ties, miss out on events and other social interactions that people limit to Facebook. But even¬†if you do leave, or if you never joined, &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.zdnet.com/article/firm-facebooks-shadow-profiles-are-frightening-dossiers-on-everyone/&#34;&gt;Facebook has a shadow profile on you&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If a friend or acquaintance has used the Find Friends functionality, or used Facebook Messenger on their phone,¬†they gave Facebook access to their Contacts. Facebook uses those names, email addresses, and phone numbers to build their shadow profiles.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/088_hu1482dd075ee48e9af8aa939642e3cffc_436367_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/088_hu1482dd075ee48e9af8aa939642e3cffc_436367_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/088_hu1482dd075ee48e9af8aa939642e3cffc_436367_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/088_hu1482dd075ee48e9af8aa939642e3cffc_436367_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/088.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;088.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Screenshot of all the different input forms for Facebook‚Äôs Find Friends, including email addresses and passwords&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following quote is nearly four years old:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúRight now commenters across the Internet will be saying, Don‚Äôt join Facebook or Delete your account. But it appears that we‚Äôre subject to Facebook‚Äôs shadow profiles whether or not we choose to participate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I feel like we‚Äôre only beginning to understand why Facebook‚Äôs data is so very valuable to advertisers, governments, app makers and malicious entities.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.zdnet.com/article/firm-facebooks-shadow-profiles-are-frightening-dossiers-on-everyone/&#34;&gt;Violet Blue, Zero Day. June 2013&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;facebook-isnt-alone&#34;&gt;Facebook isn‚Äôt alone&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facebook isn‚Äôt the only place this happens. If I go to the Spotify website, just to download Spotify, using Firefox and their &lt;a href=&#34;https://mozilla.org/lightbeam&#34;&gt;Lightbeam extension&lt;/a&gt;. (Lightbeam is a Firefox add-on. It shows you who is tracking you via third-party scripts.) Lightbeam shows me that Spotify sends my data to 25 sites.&lt;/p&gt;



