&lt;p&gt;A quick search of adsrvr.org brings me to an opt-out page which shows me this site belongs to the The Trade Desk. The Trade Desk is apparently: ‚Äútrue buying power‚Äù and ‚Äúomnichannel buying capabilities and industry ‚Äì; leading tech‚Äù Whatever that means.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/111_hu71032c7a6993d65bda5d694ec5336a4c_580327_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/111_hu71032c7a6993d65bda5d694ec5336a4c_580327_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/111_hu71032c7a6993d65bda5d694ec5336a4c_580327_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/111_hu71032c7a6993d65bda5d694ec5336a4c_580327_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/111.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;111.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Screenshot of The Trade Desk‚Äôs homepage saying they have ‚ÄúTrue Buying Power‚Äù&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&#34;https://ind.ie&#34;&gt;Ind.ie&lt;/a&gt;, we‚Äôve been doing a lot of research into trackers lately, and here‚Äôs a top tip: always check out the privacy policy. Most tracking companies are the clearest about their agendas in their privacy policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúThe Trade Desk Technology allows our Clients to buy ad space on websites for online advertising and allows for the use of proprietary and third party data in the purchase of that media.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://thetradedesk.com/general/privacy-policy&#34;&gt;The Trade Desk Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúOur Technology collects Non-Personally Identifiable Information(‚ÄúNon-PII‚Äù) that may include, but is not limited to‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your IP host address,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the date and time of the ad request,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;pages viewed,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;browser type,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the referring URL,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internet Service Provider,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;and your computer‚Äôs operating system,‚Äù&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://thetradedesk.com/general/privacy-policy&#34;&gt;The Trade Desk Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That‚Äôs a lot of your information going into the cloud. But did you notice the caveat? Non-personally identifiable information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;non-personally-identifiable-information&#34;&gt;Non-personally identifiable information&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúSuch as your IP host address, age, gender, income, education, interests and usage activity‚Ä¶‚Äù&lt;a href=&#34;http://thetradedesk.com/general/privacy-policy&#34;&gt;The Trade Desk Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take my IP address where I work in Malm√∂‚Ä¶ it can pinpoint me to exactly where I am 25% of the time. And then if you add in my age, gender and education (which is all easily available on Facebook, Linkedin, etc)‚Ä¶ How many 30 year old women who studied in Somerset in the UK are working in that building in Malm√∂ 800 miles away? It‚Äôs definitely this idiot.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/146_hu2f996eb28b1a4339b89dcf641f6e135d_455490_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/146_hu2f996eb28b1a4339b89dcf641f6e135d_455490_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/146_hu2f996eb28b1a4339b89dcf641f6e135d_455490_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/146_hu2f996eb28b1a4339b89dcf641f6e135d_455490_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/146.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;146.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;My IP address, age, gender and education overlayed on a map of Malm√∂, where I work&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But they ‚Äúdon‚Äôt share it.‚Äù ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs non-personally identifiable information.‚Äù But how true is that really? In &lt;a href=&#34;http://archive.wired.com/politics/security/commentary/securitymatters/2007/12/securitymatters_1213&#34;&gt;‚ÄòWhy ‚ÄúAnonymous‚Äù Data Sometimes Isn‚Äôt‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;, Bruce Schneier, a cryptographer, computer security and privacy expert says:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äúit takes only a small named database for someone to pry the anonymity off a much larger anonymous database‚Äù‚Äî &lt;a href=&#34;http://archive.wired.com/politics/security/commentary/securitymatters/2007/12/securitymatters_1213&#34;&gt; Bruce Schneier&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With more than one dataset, and the right algorithm, nearly any dataset can be de-anonymised. An example of these databases could be Sweden‚Äôs hitta.se, or the UK‚Äôs electoral roll. With these publicly-available databases, any or all of this data could be connected to me as a person.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/156_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_43387_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/156_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_43387_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/156_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_43387_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/156_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_43387_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/156.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;156.jpg&#39;
        alt=&#39;&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means many of these third parties can work out a lot more about me and my habits, but surely they don‚Äôt know me as‚Ä¶a person?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúFacebook knows you better than your members of your own family‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/11340166/Facebook-knows-you-better-than-your-members-of-your-own-family.html&#34;&gt;Sarah Knapton, Science Editor, Daily Telegraph.January 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Psychologists and a Computer Scientist from the Universities of Cambridge and Stanford discovered that &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pnas.org/content/112/4/1036.abstract&#34;&gt;computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúThe team found that their software was able to predict a study participant‚Äôs personality more accurately than a work colleague by analysing just 10 ‚ÄòLikes‚Äô.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/11340166/Facebook-knows-you-better-than-your-members-of-your-own-family.html&#34;&gt;Sarah Knapton, Science Editor, Daily Telegraph. January 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúInputting 70 ‚ÄòLikes‚Äô allowed it to obtain a truer picture of someone‚Äôs character than a friend or room-mate, while 150 ‚ÄòLikes‚Äô outperformed a parent, sibling or partners.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/11340166/Facebook-knows-you-better-than-your-members-of-your-own-family.html&#34;&gt;Sarah Knapton, Science Editor, Daily Telegraph. January 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;


    &lt;a
      href=&#39;http://www.pnas.org/content/112/4/1036/F2.large.jpg&#39;
    &gt;

    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
