    /&gt;
      &lt;/a&gt;


&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúIt took 300 ‚ÄòLikes‚Äô before the programme was able to judge character better than a spouse.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/11340166/Facebook-knows-you-better-than-your-members-of-your-own-family.html&#34;&gt;Sarah Knapton, Science Editor, Daily Telegraph. January 2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the introduction of Facebook reactions, there‚Äôs even more Facebook can know about you because they have more specific data. &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/facebook-reactions-%20belgian-police-warn-citizens-not-to-react-to-posts-on-social-media-a7027786.html&#34;&gt;Police in Belgium have even warned people about using Facebook reactions&lt;/a&gt;‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúBelgian police now says that the site [Facebook] is using them as a way of collecting information about people and deciding how best to advertise to them. As such, it has warned people that they should avoid using the buttons if they want to preserve their privacy.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/facebook-reactions-%20belgian-police-warn-citizens-not-to-react-to-posts-on-social-media-a7027786.html&#34;&gt;The Independent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/163_hu8a125bb0bc1a53ee00479c0d3e59c914_59945_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/163_hu8a125bb0bc1a53ee00479c0d3e59c914_59945_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/163_hu8a125bb0bc1a53ee00479c0d3e59c914_59945_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/163_hu8a125bb0bc1a53ee00479c0d3e59c914_59945_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/163.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;163.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Facebook reactions: Like, Love, Haha, Wow, Sad, Angry&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúBy limiting the number of icons to six, Facebook is counting on you to express your thoughts more easily so that the algorithms that run in the background are more effective,‚Äù the post continues. ‚ÄúBy mouse clicks you can let them know what makes you happy.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/facebook-reactions-%20belgian-police-warn-citizens-not-to-react-to-posts-on-social-media-a7027786.html&#34;&gt;The Independent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That is real information from the Belgian police. How many things have you liked on Facebook? Do you use the other reactions too?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;welcome-to-the-world-of-the-data-broker&#34;&gt;Welcome to the world of the Data Broker&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And this is why data brokers exist. They are corporations whose business it is to collect and combine data sets:&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/170_hue304c5be8eaac8b7ce14262b8bdcb975_569332_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/170_hue304c5be8eaac8b7ce14262b8bdcb975_569332_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/170_hue304c5be8eaac8b7ce14262b8bdcb975_569332_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/170_hue304c5be8eaac8b7ce14262b8bdcb975_569332_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/170.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;170.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;LexisNexis homepage&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúLexisNexis helps uncover the information that commercial organizations, government agencies and nonprofits need to get a complete picture of individuals, businesses and assets‚Ä¶‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/172_hu955081c1910fab99939d0cae647b83c2_405518_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/172_hu955081c1910fab99939d0cae647b83c2_405518_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/172_hu955081c1910fab99939d0cae647b83c2_405518_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/172_hu955081c1910fab99939d0cae647b83c2_405518_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/172.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;172.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Acxiom homepage&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúOnly Acxiom connects people across channels, time and name change at scale by linking our vast repository of offline data to the online environment‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs a big money business, and the different ways to monetise you are endless. For example, a couple of years ago, Facebook was granted a patent:&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/176_hubed1351f6bb3c2b744f4db826d36f2a8_234149_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/176_hubed1351f6bb3c2b744f4db826d36f2a8_234149_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/176_hubed1351f6bb3c2b744f4db826d36f2a8_234149_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/176_hubed1351f6bb3c2b744f4db826d36f2a8_234149_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/176.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;176.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Facebook‚Äôs patent&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúWhen an individual applies for a loan, the lender ‚Äù examines the credit ratings of members of the individual‚Äôs social network who are connected to the individual through authorized nodes. If the average credit rating of these members is at least a minimum credit score, the lender continues to process the loan application. Otherwise, the loan application is rejected.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, that means what you think it does. It means they want to approve loans based on the financial records of your Facebook friends. And would that make you think about your friends in a different light? What about when your friend unfriends you on Facebook because you‚Äôre too poor?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;governments-and-corporations&#34;&gt;Governments and corporations&lt;/h2&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/182_huc6e64c463d376d16ec2dc674e95003bf_678421_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/182_huc6e64c463d376d16ec2dc674e95003bf_678421_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/182_huc6e64c463d376d16ec2dc674e95003bf_678421_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/182_huc6e64c463d376d16ec2dc674e95003bf_678421_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/182.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;182.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Donald Trump meeting with tech leaders from Silicon Valley&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Privacy advocates have long worried about the data that is collected by corporations getting into the hands of unfriendly governments. With the political situation we find ourselves in now, those privacy advocates are unfortunately being proved right:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theverge.com/2017/1/30/14438280/trump-border-agents-search-social-media-instagram&#34;&gt;Border controls across the world using social media to discriminate against travellers&lt;/a&gt;, even demanding those under scrutiny enter their password to allow authorities access to their accounts. Of course, this disproportionately affects people of colour and other victims of bigoted profiling. &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.engadget.com/2017/02/10/inauguration-protest-arrests-lead-to-facebook-data-prosecution/&#34;&gt;People arrested during protests on Trump‚Äôs Inauguration Day had investigators requesting their data from Facebook to help incriminate them&lt;/a&gt;. And &lt;a href=&#34;https://rewire.news/article/2016/05/25/anti-choice-groups-deploy-smartphone-surveillance-target-abortion-minded-women-clinic-visits/&#34;&gt;anti-choice groups have used behavioural advertising on phones to target women in healthcare clinics&lt;/a&gt;. Erin Kissane put it best in her post on how to ‚ÄúBe More Careful on Facebook‚Äù when she said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúIf you believe Facebook will keep your data safe and never let it be used against you or your most vulnerable contacts, by governmental or private entities, you‚Äôre putting your faith in an entity that has demonstrated bad faith for years.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://incisive.nu/2017/facebook/&#34;&gt;Erin Kissane, Be More Careful on Facebook, February 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;data-grabbing-is-the-dominant-business-model-of-mainstream-technology&#34;&gt;Data grabbing is the dominant business model of mainstream technology&lt;/h2&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/190_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_115126_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/190_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_115126_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/190_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_115126_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/190_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_115126_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/190.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;190.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Data grabbing is the dominant business model of mainstream technology&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I may be spending an unequal amount of time focusing on Facebook when, grabbing your data is really the dominant business model of mainstream technology. I thought I‚Äôd insert here a list of products and services that collect your information without really needing it, but I realised it‚Äôd be unending. Instead, I‚Äôve made a list of products whose information on you would probably make you a little uncomfortable‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Google Nest&lt;/strong&gt;, home security that &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/jun/18/googles-nest-cam-always-watching-live-streaming-video&#34;&gt;will have a good look around your home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hello Barbie&lt;/strong&gt;, a doll who your kids can talk to, &lt;a href=&#34;http://europe.newsweek.com/privacy-advocates-want-take-wifi-connected-hello-barbie-o%20ine-313432&#34;&gt;recording all their responses, and sending it back to a multinational corporation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.pacif-i.io&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smart pacifier&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, in case you wanted to put a chip in your baby.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your medical records.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.digitalhealth.net/2017/03/deepmind-health-is-in-conversation-with-nhs-trusts-across-the-country/&#34;&gt;Because it‚Äôs fine if Google has those, right?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/700989404/looncup-the-worlds-first-smart-menstrual-cup&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looncup&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a smart menstrual cup! It‚Äôs one of many smart things that women can put inside themselves. (Note that most of the internet of things companies in this genre are run by men‚Ä¶)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Connect‚Äôs smart dildo&lt;/strong&gt;, which was &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.vocativ.com/358530/smart-dildo-company-sued-for-tracking-users-habits/&#34;&gt;found to be tracking its users‚Äô habits&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And have you ever wondered how many calories you‚Äôre burning during intercourse? How many thrusts? Speed of your thrusts? The duration of your sessions? Frequency? How many different positions you use in the period of a week, month or year? Then you want the &lt;a href=&#34;http://britishcondoms.uk/i-con-smart-condom.html&#34;&gt;iCondom&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/211_hude0385883d796d7c6ffa92cd094d152a_311242_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/211_hude0385883d796d7c6ffa92cd094d152a_311242_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/211_hude0385883d796d7c6ffa92cd094d152a_311242_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/211_hude0385883d796d7c6ffa92cd094d152a_311242_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/211.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;211.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;iCondom packaging&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That‚Äôs assuming you want all that information shared with advertisers, insurers, your government, and whoever else wants to buy it‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Needless to say, beware the &lt;em&gt;Internet Of Things That Spy On You&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/212_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_81032_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/212_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_81032_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/212_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_81032_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/212_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_81032_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/212.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;212.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Beware the Internet Of Things That Spy On You&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;learning-about-yourself--corporations-learning-about-you&#34;&gt;Learning about yourself ‚â† corporations learning about you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of these products are really cool. I was an early adopter of fitness trackers. I love to know data about myself, and use that to encourage better habits. Learning about yourself does not have to mean that corporations learn about you too. None of these Internet Of Things products &lt;em&gt;need&lt;/em&gt; to share your data back to their various clouds, or with any other parties, to be convenient to you. These are physical products. They have a clear option for a business model, they can be sold for money.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/213_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108575_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/213_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108575_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/213_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108575_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/213_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108575_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/213.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;213.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Learning about yourself is not equal to corporations learning about you&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not to mention, collecting information about people can be dangerous. Any organisation collecting data has to be able to keep it secure and safe from malicious parties. Glow, a pregnancy app, &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.consumerreports.org/mobile-security-software/glow-pregnancy-app-exposed-women-to-privacy-threats/&#34;&gt;was discovered to have vulnerabilities&lt;/a&gt; making it easy for stalkers, online bullies, or identity thieves to use the information they gathered to harm Glow‚Äôs users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;chilling-effect&#34;&gt;Chilling Effect&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if you‚Äôre aware that these products are spying on you, and you continue to use them, they can still affect you in adverse ways. They can create a ‚Äúchilling effect.‚Äù A chilling effect is where a person may behave differently from how they would naturally, because of the legal and social implications of their actions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the other side, products with information about you are far more able to manipulate you. Products like digital assistants such as Amazon‚Äôs Alexa or Google Now‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúAs the digital butler expands its role in our daily lives, it can alter our worldview. By crafting notes for us, and suggesting ‚Äúlikes‚Äù for other posts it wrote for other people, our personal assistant can e ectively manipulate us through this stimulation.‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wired.com/2016/11/subtle-ways-digital-assistant-might-manipulate/&#34;&gt;Maurice E. Stucke and Ariel Ezrachi, The Subtle Ways Your Digital Assistant Might Manipulate You, November 2016&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;fake-news&#34;&gt;Fake News!&lt;/h2&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/220_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_58296_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/220_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_58296_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/220_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_58296_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/220_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_58296_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/220.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;220.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Fake News!&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve got fake news in the title of this talk, but what does all of this have to do with fake news?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First of all we have to look at what constitutes fake news. Fake news is content presented as a news story but with no grounding in reality, let alone journalistic rigour. Fake news roughly fits into three categories:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.Real issues exaggerated to distract you, such as issues that are exaggerated to distract the public.
2. Propaganda, weaponised speech delivered to achieve a political aim ‚Äì; a mixture of truth, exaggeration and deception.
3. &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dw.com/en/fake-news-is-a-red-herring/a-37269377&#34;&gt;‚ÄúDisinformatzya,‚Äù&lt;/a&gt; false content deliberately created to muddy the waters of informed public opinion, to make you distrust everything in the news&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;adtech&#34;&gt;Adtech!&lt;/h3&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/226_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_60116_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/226_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_60116_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/226_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_60116_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/226_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_60116_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/226.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;226.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Adtech!&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have to ask why have all of these forms of not-news dressed up as news become popular? The answer is adtech:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúThis form of digital advertising [adtech] has turned into a massive industry, driven by an assumption that the best advertising is also the most targeted, the most real-time, the most data-driven, the most personal‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://artplusmarketing.com/brands-need-to-fire-adtech-f9d18edd2f9a&#34;&gt;Doc Searls, Brands need to fire adtech, March 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The problem is that adtech powers the ads that show alongside everything. Adtech is behind the pay-per-click ads that show you things that are relevant to the article or to you.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/228_hu89f17a9faf4bba2890499301e66abcc3_372499_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/228_hu89f17a9faf4bba2890499301e66abcc3_372499_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/228_hu89f17a9faf4bba2890499301e66abcc3_372499_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/228_hu89f17a9faf4bba2890499301e66abcc3_372499_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/228.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;228.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Facebook ad alongside Facebook feed&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adtech is the ads that follow you around the web.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/229_hue1c44a2a1b0da278403466803aed794f_518806_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/229_hue1c44a2a1b0da278403466803aed794f_518806_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/229_hue1c44a2a1b0da278403466803aed794f_518806_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/229_hue1c44a2a1b0da278403466803aed794f_518806_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/229.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;229.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Amazon ads for things you‚Äôve browsed following you around the web&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adtech is the clickbait of intriguing stories that are sometimes dressed up as ‚ÄúOther articles you might like‚Äù, ‚ÄúPromoted links,‚Äù or ‚ÄúSponsored content.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/230_hu5de7c5f479d4429fdfdb4d9a25fbbb8b_423532_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/230_hu5de7c5f479d4429fdfdb4d9a25fbbb8b_423532_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/230_hu5de7c5f479d4429fdfdb4d9a25fbbb8b_423532_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/230_hu5de7c5f479d4429fdfdb4d9a25fbbb8b_423532_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/230.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;230.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Outbrain ‚Äúpromoted links from around the web‚Äù on The Guardian&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚Äú1. It‚Äôs adtech that spies on people and violates their privacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It‚Äôs adtech that‚Äôs full of fraud and a vector for malware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It‚Äôs adtech that incentivizes publications to prioritize ‚Äúcontent generation‚Äù over journalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It‚Äôs adtech that gives fake news a business model, because the fake is easier to produce than the real, and it pays just as well.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://artplusmarketing.com/brands-need-to-fire-adtech-f9d18edd2f9a&#34;&gt;Doc Searls, Brands need to fire adtech, March 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wired.com/2017/02/veles-macedonia-fake-news/&#34;&gt;Wired talked to a Macedonian teenager about his lucrative business posting disinformatyza&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúHe posted the link on Facebook, seeding it within various groups devoted to American politics; to his astonish¬≠ment, it was shared around 800 times. That month‚ÄîFebruary 2016‚ÄîBoris made more than $150 off the Google ads on his website. Considering this to be the best possible use of his time, he stopped going to high school.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And on top of that, as Evgeny Morozov said in the Guardian:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúThe problem is not fake news but the speed and ease of its dissemination, and it exists primarily because today‚Äôs digital capitalism makes it extremely profitable ‚Äì look at Google and Facebook ‚Äì to produce and circulate false but click-worthy narratives.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/jan/08/blaming-fake-news-not-the-answer-democracy-crisis&#34;&gt;Evgeny Morozov, Moral panic over fake news hides the real enemy ‚Äì the digital giants, January 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But how do we solve this problem that is now at the core of journalism?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúSolving the problem of sensationalistic, click-driven journalism likely requires a new business model for news that focuses on its civic importance above profitability.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dw.com/en/fake-news-is-a-red-herring/a-37269377&#34;&gt;Ethan Zuckerman, Fake news is a red herring, January 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not-news is causing problems for the advertisers too, with &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2017/mar/19/google-braces-for-questions-as-more-big-name-firms-pull-adverts&#34;&gt;some advertisers stopping using adtech platforms after their products appeared alongside undesirable and extreme content&lt;/a&gt;. But I‚Äôm not so sure this will make much of a difference to the pockets of the adtech makers. I wonder is this adtech business model too lucrative to change?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-can-we-do-to-block-clickbait-and-fake-news-from-our-lives&#34;&gt;What can we do to block clickbait and fake news from our lives?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to think about what can we do &lt;em&gt;now&lt;/em&gt; to block the clickbait and fake news from our lives? Assuming our friends aren‚Äôt forcing us on to it via social media‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;ad-blockers&#34;&gt;Ad Blockers?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Could ad blockers be the answer? Many people have started blocking trackers using ad blockers. The key issue with this is that &lt;strong&gt;ads are not the problem. Trackers are the problem.&lt;/strong&gt; The third-party tracking scripts are the problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&#34;https://ind.ie&#34;&gt;Ind.ie&lt;/a&gt;, we‚Äôve been doing &lt;a href=&#34;https://better.fyi&#34;&gt;research into trackers&lt;/a&gt;, and we found some of the most used third-party scripts on the web:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;google-analytics.com‚Äî64.1% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;doubleclick.net‚Äî54.4% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;google.com‚Äî41.9% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gstatic.com‚Äî32.8% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;googleadservices.com‚Äî32.3% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;facebook.com‚Äî29.0% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;googlesyndication.com‚Äî26.9% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;facebook.net‚Äî26.4% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;google.se‚Äî23.0% of sites researched&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So far, we‚Äôve found around 78.5% of trackers from the top 10,000 sites come from Google. All of these sites set third-party cookies and/or tracking pixels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cookies themselves aren‚Äôt inherently problematic. First-party cookies can be useful in storing your username at logins or remembering your preferred language on a site. But we don‚Äôt want or need the bad third-party cookies that are just sitting there following us around and spying on everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;surveillance-capitalism&#34;&gt;Surveillance Capitalism&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is what Shoshana Zuboff coined as ‚ÄúSurveillance capitalism.‚Äù Also know as ‚Äúcorporate surveillance‚Äù or more simply, ‚Äúpeople farming.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/260_hudf0fd0e130647ea56164edb57d6e4d71_897236_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/260_hudf0fd0e130647ea56164edb57d6e4d71_897236_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/260_hudf0fd0e130647ea56164edb57d6e4d71_897236_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/260_hudf0fd0e130647ea56164edb57d6e4d71_897236_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/260.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;260.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Horrible clickbait on LifeBuzz such as ‚ÄúMirror cakes are the new food porn and they WILL excite you‚Äù&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some people recognising this problem have started using ad blockers to block ads and third party scripts. As consumers of the web, we often use ad blockers, but as web builders, they can inconvenience us if they block what we‚Äôve created.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When it comes to ad blockers, it bears repeating: ads are not the problem. Trackers are the problem. There are some horrifying ads and clickbait out there, but many of these blockers are not doing exactly what you think they are. For example, [Adblock Plus](&lt;a href=&#34;https://adblockplus.org/en/acceptable-ads%22&#34;&gt;https://adblockplus.org/en/acceptable-ads&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt; rel=&amp;ldquo;nofollow) has a whitelist called Acceptable Ads which are ads and trackers that they just let through:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äúwe share a vision with the majority of our users that not all ads are equally annoying‚Äù‚Äî[Acceptable Ads criteria](&lt;a href=&#34;https://adblockplus.org/en/acceptable-ads#criteria%22&#34;&gt;https://adblockplus.org/en/acceptable-ads#criteria&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt; rel=&amp;ldquo;nofollow)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acceptable ads are largely included under the criteria that they‚Äôre not too dominant or annoying. But as I said before, annoying ads are not the problem. Trackers are the problem. And there‚Äôs nothing in the Acceptable Ads criteria about ads tracking you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äúwe are being paid by some larger properties that serve non-intrusive advertisements that want to participate in the Acceptable Ads initiative‚Äù‚Äî[Acceptable Ads Agreements](&lt;a href=&#34;https://adblockplus.org/acceptable-ads-agreements%22&#34;&gt;https://adblockplus.org/acceptable-ads-agreements&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt; rel=&amp;ldquo;nofollow)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What‚Äôs worse is that larger companies are paying for their ads to be shown. Including Google‚Äôs ads (and trackers). And we know how wide Google‚Äôs trackers reach‚Ä¶ Worse still, &lt;a href=&#34;http://boingboing.net/2016/09/13/adblock-now-selling-ads.html&#34;&gt;now AdBlock Plus is even selling ads to replace the ones it blocks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The anti-annoying-ad argument is distracting us from the real problems. Ad networks aren‚Äôt inherently bad. For example, &lt;a href=&#34;http://decknetwork.net&#34;&gt;The Deck&lt;/a&gt; (now sadly closed) was an ad network which targeted its audience by only being used on specialist sites. And &lt;a href=&#34;http://decknetwork.net/privacy/&#34;&gt;they were fine with knowing nothing&lt;/a&gt; about the individuals who viewed those ads:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt track our readers in any way or allow any other behind-the-scenes shenanigans. We just serve useful, relevant ads in a simple, unobtrusive way to support independent publishers.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;http://decknetwork.net/privacy/&#34;&gt;The Deck Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;can-we-still-have-behavioural-ads&#34;&gt;Can we still have behavioural ads?&lt;/h3&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/281_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_94003_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/281_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_94003_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/281_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_94003_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/281_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_94003_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/281.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;281.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Advertising does not need to phone home to the cloud&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The benefit of The Deck was that it showed static ads to a niche audience, but what about behavioural ads? We could still show relevant ads based on behaviour. Advertising does not need to phone home to the cloud. You could still have behavioural advertising that keeps your information private by doing all the behavioural analysis and decision-making on the device itself. So it could work in theory, but who is going to use these systems when your personal information is so lucrative?&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/275_hu852340e29baa4566ff2744791a7bb9b4_366022_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/275_hu852340e29baa4566ff2744791a7bb9b4_366022_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/275_hu852340e29baa4566ff2744791a7bb9b4_366022_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/275_hu852340e29baa4566ff2744791a7bb9b4_366022_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/275.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;275.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;The Deck‚Äôs privacy policy which said ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre fine with knowing nothing‚Äù&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;analytics&#34;&gt;Analytics&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There‚Äôs one third-party script that almost all of us put on our sites‚Ä¶ analytics. Considering everything we‚Äôve looked at so far, how can we use analytics more ethically?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remember that stat from before, that 64.1% of the top 10,000 sites are using Google Analytics? How many of those sites do you visit? What has that told Google about you? How does that make you feel about using analytics on your own sites? Is it ethical or necessary to track visitors to our site? This isn‚Äôt a problem with a yes or no answer, but we need to consider these questions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;ethics-in-technology&#34;&gt;Ethics in technology&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of these issues I‚Äôve discussed fall under the bracket of ethics. Ethics are defined as ‚Äúa set of moral principles, especially ones relating to or affirming a specified group, field, or form of conduct.‚Äù So how do they relate to our everyday work in the web and technology industries?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;we-build-the-new-everyday-things&#34;&gt;We build the new everyday things&lt;/h3&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/290_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_82475_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/290_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_82475_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/290_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_82475_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/290_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_82475_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/290.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;290.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We build the new everyday things&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Us people building the web are building the new everyday things. We‚Äôre building the new infrastructure that powers our society. Much like other systems we use every day that we might pay taxes for: roads, clean water, waste removal, police, fire and rescue services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How much time do you spend using a road every day? On the average day, I‚Äôll cycle to the office, walk to the supermarket, that‚Äôs around 90 minutes using roads and paths. When &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.iabuk.net/about/press/archive/definitive-time-people-spend-online-2hrs-51-mins-a-day&#34;&gt;the average person spends 2 hours 51 minutes of time per day on the internet&lt;/a&gt;, it becomes clear how much impact our work can have. And that‚Äôs why we need to take responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/295_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_73029_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/295_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_73029_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/295_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_73029_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/295_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_73029_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/295.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;295.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We need to take responsibility&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to take care of people using the new infrastructure we‚Äôre building. Having responsibility isn‚Äôt usually fun, but it is necessary. And this is why we need ethics, a kind of code of conduct for the people in our position of power of building the web. Mike Monteiro points out how hypocritical we can be‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äú[W]hen other industries behave unethically we get upset. Yet, many of us seem to have no problem behaving unethically ourselves. We design databases for collecting information, without giving a second thought what that information will be used for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a community have we fallen to the level of debating the importance of ethics that‚Äôs usually reserved for politicians, bankers, hedge fund managers, pimps, and bookies?‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://deardesignstudent.com/ethics-cant-be-a-side-hustle-b9e78c090aee&#34;&gt;Mike Monteiro, Ethics can‚Äôt be a side hustle, March 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;use-your-powers-for-good&#34;&gt;Use your powers for good&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need designers and developers to use their powers for good.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/298_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_69755_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/298_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_69755_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/298_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_69755_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/298_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_69755_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/298.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;298.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Use your powers for good&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This come with the understanding that code is not neutral, that whatever we build comes with our biases. We all have biases. And that code is political. I‚Äôm not saying that your code is politically aligned to a particular party, you do not need to have the same political affiliations as me to believe that your world outlook has an impact on the things you create.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/302_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87343_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/302_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87343_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/302_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87343_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/302_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87343_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/302.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;302.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Your world outlook has an impact on the things you create&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What happens when &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/1/8880363/google-apologizes-photos-app-tags-two-%20black-people-gorillas&#34;&gt;someone only tests their algorithms on the other white people around them&lt;/a&gt;? Or &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cambridge-paediatrician-8217-s-outrage-pure-gym/%20story-26188693-detail/story.html&#34;&gt;when a programmer makes a security system that assumes there are no women doctors&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We‚Äôre not just building cool stuff for fun, we‚Äôre building things that affect other peoples‚Äô lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-ethical-design-manifesto&#34;&gt;The Ethical Design Manifesto&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Ind.ie, we decided we need an &lt;a href=&#34;https://ind.ie/ethical-design&#34;&gt;Ethical Design Manifesto&lt;/a&gt; for the things we use every day:&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;371.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;The 3 Rs of Ethical Design&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are decentralised, private, open, interoperable, accessible, secure and sustainable. Because that means a product will respect human rights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;decentralised&#34;&gt;Decentralised&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Decentralisation is something we talk about as developers as being a good thing because we don‚Äôt like to rely on centralised systems. It‚Äôs why we don‚Äôt hotlink all our images and scripts from other sites, and why nobody gets any work done when Github is down. We understand that if it‚Äôs not on our computers or servers, it‚Äôs not under our control. But for some reason we‚Äôre happy to give &lt;em&gt;corporations&lt;/em&gt; control over all of our data.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/317_hu545c15c273fd376bba9903166fa5d032_192471_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/317_hu545c15c273fd376bba9903166fa5d032_192471_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/317_hu545c15c273fd376bba9903166fa5d032_192471_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/317_hu545c15c273fd376bba9903166fa5d032_192471_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/317.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;317.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;GitHub‚Äôs timeout status page&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With control over data comes power. After the Snowden revelations, people were rightly outraged by how much access our governments had to our browsing information, but not so many people were angry with the corporations who were collecting that information, and handing it right over to the governments. As Bruce Schneier said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄòThe NSA woke up and said ‚ÄúCorporations are spying on the Internet, let‚Äôs get ourselves a copy‚Äù‚Äô‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.schneier.com/news/archives/2014/04/surveillance_is_the.html&#34;&gt;Bruce Schneier&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;private&#34;&gt;Private&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are private. Privacy can come as a result of decentralisation: if your data is only on your device, it‚Äôs private to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;open&#34;&gt;Open&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build open products. ‚ÄúFree and open‚Äù or ‚Äúopen source‚Äù mean that anyone with sufficient technical knowledge can take the code from some software and make their own version. For free. When a product is free and open, it means you can trust it to some degree, because if one version goes in a direction you don‚Äôt like, you can use a different version. Though it‚Äôs worth noting that developers are much more of a position to do this than most people who use computers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;interoperable&#34;&gt;Interoperable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are interoperable. Back in the day, we had phones where you enter all your contacts in manually. It took ages, and then when you got a new phone, you‚Äôd have to enter your contacts in all over again. It was a frustrating experience. But using a SIM card to transfer the contacts across made it much easier because SIM cards are interoperable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another example of where we don‚Äôt have interoperability is in ‚Äúwalled gardens.‚Äù It is very common for corporations to want to lock you into their own beautiful ecosystem. That‚Äôs what can make it a nightmare switching between Apple and Android.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;accessible&#34;&gt;Accessible&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are accessible. Accessibility is making something available to as many people as possible. To make our products more accessible we need to consider diversity, cost, and catering to a variety of needs that aren‚Äôt necessarily the same as our own. We must never stop looking for ways to make our work more accessible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;secure&#34;&gt;Secure&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are secure. In the age of https on everything, we‚Äôre more clued up about security. However, security is also confused and conflated with privacy. For example, Google encrypted email and said ‚Äúyay! all your stuff is now safe and private from hackers!‚Äù But that email is not encrypted and private &lt;em&gt;from Google&lt;/em&gt;, it just protects your information in transit between you and Google.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;sustainable&#34;&gt;Sustainable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to build products that are economically, environmentally and culturally sustainable. When a product is sustainable, you know it‚Äôs worth putting your time into using it. The product isn‚Äôt going to disappear tomorrow with all your information and hard work down the drain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the key elements of sustainability is that a product has a viable long-term business model. (That doesn‚Äôt rely on selling your data!) If a startup has been given a huge amount of venture capital without having a business model, chances are they‚Äôre not sustainable,¬†and it‚Äôs highly likely they‚Äôre going to rely on selling your data for profit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;functional-convenient-and-reliable&#34;&gt;Functional, convenient and reliable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When we‚Äôve ensured our product respects human rights, we can work on making it functional, convenient and reliable. Doing so respects human effort, and these are generally the goals most of us are reaching for when we‚Äôre building things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a product is functional, convenient and reliable, it actually does the thing, it does the thing in a way that doesn‚Äôt get in your way, and it does that thing reliably again and again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;delightful&#34;&gt;Delightful&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once our product respects human rights and human effort, we can layer the delight on top, to make our product delightful, respecting human experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delightful isn‚Äôt just making products fun and fluffy. It‚Äôs about creating a genuinely great experience, which is reinforced because it‚Äôs built upon the strong foundation of respecting your effort and rights. Basecamp is a good example of this, where they have little touches of delight.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;figure&gt;


    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/368_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_238419_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/368_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_238419_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/368_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_238419_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/368_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_238419_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/368.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;368.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Screenshot of Basecamp schedule with a cute pen drawing of a Basecamp icon toasting marshmallows over a campfire&#39;
    /&gt;

    &lt;figcaption&gt;


      &lt;p&gt;The Basecamp schedule when you haven‚Äôt had any past events¬†yet&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basecamp can only get away with whimsical details because they already respect your human rights and effort. As &lt;a href=&#34;https://medium.com/@sara_ann_marie/dear-tech-you-suck-at-delight-86382d101575&#34;&gt;Sara Wachter-Boettcher wrote in a fabulous article&lt;/a&gt; last year:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúQuit painting a thin layer of cuteness over fundamentally broken interfaces.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://medium.com/@sara_ann_marie/dear-tech-you-suck-at-delight-86382d101575&#34;&gt;Dear Tech, You Suck at Delight, Sara Wachter-Boettcher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Layering cuteness on top it is not a solution to a badly-built product, it‚Äôs just a way to make ourselves feel better about the problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Ind.ie, we call Respecting human rights, Respecting human effort, and Respecting human experience the 3 Rs of Ethical Design.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_191287_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/371.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;371.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;The 3 Rs of Ethical Design&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many modern products don‚Äôt respect our human rights. Instead they‚Äôre built on the backs of the humans that use them. These (often-Silicon Valley) products may respect human experience and human effort, but they take advantage of their users. They don‚Äôt give them privacy or security, interoperability or open technologies. Very rarely are their products accessible or sustainable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But as an industry, we hail these products. We call them the ‚Äúdisruptors.‚Äù In the dictionary, ‚Äúto disrupt‚Äù means ‚Äúto interrupt (an event, activity, or process) by causing a disturbance or problem.‚Äù¬†People making these products call themselves disruptors because they ‚Äúdisrupt‚Äù a market. They take down existing sustainable businesses and kill them off. They monopolise and they dump. We need to disrupt the disruptors. We need to disrupt their disruption.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/375_hubfb60b80b607797eef2c981d83501249_1440696_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/375_hubfb60b80b607797eef2c981d83501249_1440696_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/375_hubfb60b80b607797eef2c981d83501249_1440696_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/375_hubfb60b80b607797eef2c981d83501249_1440696_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/375.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;375.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Silicon Valley landscape&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;we-need-to-ask-ourselves-these-questions&#34;&gt;We need to ask ourselves these questions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to ask ourselves these questions about what we build. Because we are the gatekeepers of what we create. We don‚Äôt have to add tracking to everything, it‚Äôs already gotten out of our control.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/379_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108705_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/379_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108705_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/379_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108705_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/379_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_108705_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/379.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;379.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We are the gatekeepers of what we create&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The business model of the organisations we work for is our business. If what we are building is harming people, we can‚Äôt blame someone else for that. We can‚Äôt defer responsibility for the products we build, that‚Äôs how bad things happen.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/381_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_72413_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/381_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_72413_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/381_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_72413_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/381_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_72413_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/381.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;381.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We can‚Äôt defer responsibility&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some people say to me ‚Äúbut if I don‚Äôt like what Google/Facebook/Other Corporations are doing, &lt;em&gt;surely&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;I&lt;/em&gt; don‚Äôt have to use their services‚Ä¶?‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nope. As I said before, social networks are part of society now. Email, booking services, ecommerce are our new everyday things. If I stopped using every site that is sharing my data with Google, I‚Äôd be using less than 25% of the web. And I couldn‚Äôt use email. We deserve to be able to take part in society, and use everyday things without our privacy being compromised.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/386_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_133370_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/386_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_133370_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/386_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_133370_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/386_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_133370_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/386.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;386.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We deserve to be able to take part in society, and use everyday things, without our privacy being compromised&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another thing I often hear is ‚Äúwhat if &lt;em&gt;I&lt;/em&gt; trust Google/Facebook/Other Corporation with my data?‚Äù Seriously people, Google isn‚Äôt your lover, you shouldn‚Äôt &lt;em&gt;have&lt;/em&gt; to trust them. Why are we so loyal to faceless corporations?&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/390_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_95763_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/390_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_95763_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/390_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_95763_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/390_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_95763_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/390.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;390.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;We need to design and build systems that don‚Äôt need to be trusted&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to design and build systems that don‚Äôt need to be trusted. If it fits with the Ethical Design Manifesto, you don‚Äôt need to trust it, you own your own data, and you can easily go elsewhere if you‚Äôre no longer satisfied.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/393_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87591_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/393_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87591_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/393_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87591_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/393_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_87591_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/393.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;393.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Not worrying about your data is privilege&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs important to realise that not worrying about your data is privilege. If you don‚Äôt worry about corporations (and by extension, governments) having access to your data, you are privileged. And quite possibly just foolish. What if you lived in a country where your sexual preference is illegal? What if you lived in a country that wants to deport people with your ethnic background? What if you lived in a country where your religious beliefs can get you killed? What if you needed a loan and your friends were considered too poor? What if you needed medical treatment but your medical insurance considered your habits made you too high risk?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look at the world around us, any of these things could happen tomorrow. If you want to think about it in terms of how trackers affect you, you need to fear for your future self.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/396_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_104820_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/396_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_104820_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/396_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_104820_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/396_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_104820_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/396.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;396.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;You‚Äôre not just making these decisions for yourself&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You also need to bear in mind that you‚Äôre not making these decisions for yourself. If you use Gmail, you are swapping free email for the data of everyone you exchange emails with. If you support your business with tracking, you are making that decision for your visitors. It‚Äôs invisible, and it‚Äôs opt-in by default. Is that fair?&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1280&#39; height=&#39;720&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/397_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_119412_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/397_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_119412_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/397_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_119412_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/397_hu6642974bf16ed882bf8486f57a8a55c3_119412_1200x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 1200w,/digital-assistants-facebook-quizzes-and-fake-news-you-wont-believe-what-happens-next/397.jpg 1280w&#39;
      src=&#39;397.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;If you support your business with tracking, you are making that decision for your visitors&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As creators we need to make wise decisions on behalf of our visitors. We can be the gatekeepers of harmful decisions. If making these decisions becomes a battle you have to fight with the top of your organisation, there might just be something wrong with the business model. An organisation that makes its money by tracking people, whether they‚Äôre doing it themselves, or getting something in exchange for adding scripts to their site, is not going to want to change. They may even find it impossible to change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As people become more aware of these issues, we need to be careful that if an organisation does appear to change, it‚Äôs not just superficial, that they‚Äôre not misdirecting us, or telling us something is better when it‚Äôs just bad in a different way. Like &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wired.com/2014/11/whatsapp-encrypted-messaging/&#34;&gt;when WhatsApp switched on end-to-end encryption for hundreds of millions of users&lt;/a&gt;. So many people said ‚ÄúYay! They‚Äôre the good guys!‚Äù But as &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.privateinternetaccess.com/blog/2014/11/whatsapp-encryption-shows-value-of-metadata/&#34;&gt;Rick Falkvinge said on his blog‚Ä¶&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ÄúWould Facebook really allow WhatsApp to throw away the business value in a 19-billion acquisition? Of course it wouldn‚Äôt. This demonstrates that the snoop value was in the metadata all along: the knowledge of who talks to whom, when, how, and how often. Not in the actual words communicated.‚Äù‚Äî&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.privateinternetaccess.com/blog/2014/11/whatsapp-encryption-shows-value-of-metadata/&#34;&gt;Rick Falkvinge&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And surprise! &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theverge.com/2016/8/25/12638698/whatsapp-to-start-sharing-user-data-with-facebook&#34;&gt;WhatsApp is now sharing user data with Facebook&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And remember &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theverge.com/2016/5/18/11701030/google-io-2016-keynote-highlights-announcements-recap&#34;&gt;when Google‚Äôs Allo was heralded for its privacy features?&lt;/a&gt; Turns out, &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theverge.com/2016/9/21/12994362/allo-privacy-message-logs-google&#34;&gt;that was just a bit of announcement &lt;abbr title=&#34;public relations&#34;&gt;PR&lt;/abbr&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can learn about the value of metadata by watching the fantastic documentary, &lt;a href=&#34;http://agoodamerican.org&#34;&gt;A Good American&lt;/a&gt;. In this film, Bill Binney, working on surveillance for the US, says that meta information is the most valuable information that the &lt;abbr title=&#34;National Security Agency of the US&#34;&gt;NSA&lt;/abbr&gt; can collect. Without meta data, surveilling people is like looking for a needle in a haystack. (I also recommend the recent Oliver Stone &lt;a href=&#34;https://snowdenfilm.com&#34;&gt;Snowden&lt;/a&gt; film for learning about how corporate surveillance and government surveillance come together.)&lt;/p&gt;


    &lt;a
      href=&#39;https://better.fyi/spotlight/&#39;
    &gt;

