&lt;p&gt;Originally posted on the¬†&lt;a href=&#34;https://forum.ind.ie/t/laura-s-diary-tuesday-1st-march-2016/1099&#34;&gt;Ind.ie forum at¬†https://forum.ind.ie/t/laura-s-diary-tuesday-1st-march-2016/1099&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/diary-1st-march-2016/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòDiary, 1st March 2016‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was just asked, amongst a couple of other questions, what advice I would give to aspiring designers or typographers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With my mind focused on the aspiration part, I started writing an answer based on finding your own way of working through studying others, not copying‚Ä¶ And then I realised it was a bit &lt;em&gt;superficial&lt;/em&gt;. What‚Äôs the biggest problem with young designers today? They‚Äôre coin-operated&lt;a href=&#34;#coin-operated&#34;&gt;*&lt;/a&gt;. So I wrote what I hope is slightly better advice:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be ethical. Design is a great power where you can choose to instruct and manipulate others into thinking, feeling, and acting. Use those powers for good, don‚Äôt promote or help those whose business and goals harm people. Work hard to build a society you want to inhabit in the long term. Don‚Äôt underestimate your own impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* &lt;a href=&#34;https://ar.al&#34;&gt;Aral&lt;/a&gt; came up with that term. I just love it.&lt;/p&gt;
