&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/what-advice-do-you-give-to-aspiring-designers-or-typographers/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòWhat advice do you give to aspiring designers or typographers?‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs nearly time! We‚Äôre moving to Sweden next Tuesday, and it‚Äôs currently at equal parts exciting and stressful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The storage locker in Brighton is almost empty, and we‚Äôve stashed all our sentimental stuff‚Äîthe things you want to keep, but probably aren‚Äôt worth putting in a suitcase to a foreign land‚Äîat my family‚Äôs house. We‚Äôre only taking a couple of suitcases of clothes, our work equipment, and of course Oskar. If we can squeeze Aral‚Äôs fancy Anglepoise lamp and a few nice bits of artwork into the pet transportation van, then we‚Äôll have those along too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Speaking of pet transportation, Oskar and I will be making our way to Sweden by road with pet couriers. It‚Äôs not cheap, but it means that I don‚Äôt have to drive across five countries on the weird side of the road, and me and my pup get to travel together. It‚Äôs going to be a long trip, with at least one overnight in Germany, so I might keep myself occupied by blogging the experience as we go‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the admin and accounting side, Aral and I are taking this ‚Äúfresh start‚Äù opportunity to wind down our own limited companies that we used for consultancy/freelancing, and simplifying our accounting. Neither of us are doing anything that isn‚Äôt in some way related to Ind.ie, so there‚Äôs no point us spending money on maintaining all the accounts. That‚Äôs also particularly good news for me, as it should lessen my admin tasks and leave me more time to work on design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One week to go!&lt;/p&gt;
