&lt;h2 id=&#34;em-classnotenote-ive-been-writing-diary-entries-on-the-indie-forum-for-a-while-now-ive-decided-to-start-sharing-these-on-my-site-now-too-as-ive-not-been-posting-much-else-they-have-bonus-dog-photosem&#34;&gt;&lt;em class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;Note: I‚Äôve been writing diary entries on the Ind.ie forum for a while now. I‚Äôve decided to start sharing these on my site now too, as I‚Äôve not been posting much else! (They have bonus dog photos.)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve been meaning to write a diary entry for ages, and 8am on a Friday morning is the first opportunity I‚Äôve had to get to it (and I‚Äôve already been working for an hour‚Ä¶)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything is going well. You might‚Äôve heard that we‚Äôve decided to move to Sweden. Our visit at the end of January saw us finding a beautiful apartment in Davidshalltorg in Malm√∂, and the wonderful people at Media Evolution City going out of their way to organise us an office space where Oskar can join us. It‚Äôs been an arduous six months, and we‚Äôre really excited to move to such a friendly and welcoming space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs been a busy few weeks, with us both working hard on the hush-hush project (not long to go!) Aral speaking in Amsterdam, our two-night house-hunting trip to Malm√∂, and my speaking on two panels this week. Now we have just over two weeks to move everything we need to Sweden, and sort everything else. Including transporting Oskar across 5 countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To that end, &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/office-furniture-for-sale/&#34;&gt;we‚Äôre selling some of the stuff from our storage room&lt;/a&gt; on the 13th February. If you‚Äôre interested in any of it, &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:laura@ind.ie&#34;&gt;give me a shout&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
