&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve had a DSLR for nearly a year now. And I still only ever use it on the Auto modes. I studied photography (with film cameras) during my Art Foundation course ~10 years ago, but I think any decent photos were mostly luck, and I can‚Äôt remember much of it. So when Ashley set up her &lt;a href=&#34;http://girlwithacamera.co.uk/courses/&#34;&gt;Girl With A Camera Course&lt;/a&gt;, ‚ÄúFor the beginner photographer who wants to pick up their camera more,‚Äù I was instantly sold!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over the next month, I‚Äôm going to try to blog some of my photos taken during Ashley‚Äôs exercises (and hopefully lots more that I‚Äôve taken for fun!) Maybe I‚Äôll be able to ditch the Auto modes by the end of it. I‚Äôve not edited any of these photos yet, as tempting as it is, as I want to wait til we get to that bit of the course!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first task was to switch my camera to manual‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;

