&lt;h2 id=&#34;less-about-me&#34;&gt;Less about me‚Ä¶&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The site¬†previously had loads of ‚Äúabout‚Äù content. There was a ordinary about page, then my skills, who I work with, what I do, and separate pages detailing my main areas of work. These are all now streamlined and redirected into a properly up-to-date &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/about-me/&#34; title=&#34;About Me&#34;&gt;about page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;navigation-accessibility&#34;&gt;Navigation accessibility&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently I‚Äôve been getting my head around &lt;a href=&#34;https://dev.opera.com/articles/introduction-to-wai-aria/&#34;&gt;WAI-ARIA&lt;/a&gt;. It‚Äôs a very valuable way to help make more modern interactive elements of your site accessible to assistive devices. This was massively helped by the wonder Heydon Pickering, who sent me this tweet:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;[@laurakalbag](https://twitter.com/laurakalbag) Hey Laura. Know you‚Äôre big on [#a11y](https://twitter.com/hashtag/a11y?src=hash), so thought you may want to try [http://t.co/iiYoaLRYbp](http://t.co/iiYoaLRYbp) to fix your site‚Äôs dropdown.
&lt;p&gt;‚Äî Hayden StandardAware (@heydonworks) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/heydonworks/status/533171711030882304&#34;&gt;November 14, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôm just ashamed that it took me so long to get around to it. Now, thanks to Heydon‚Äôs fantastic rundown of &lt;a href=&#34;http://heydonworks.com/practical_aria_examples/#progressive-collapsibles&#34;&gt;Practical Aria Examples&lt;/a&gt;, I‚Äôm using &lt;code&gt;aria-controls&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;aria-hidden&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;aria-expanded&lt;/code&gt; to great effect.&lt;/p&gt;

