&lt;p&gt;In the previous design of the site, I used brightly coloured backgrounds with white text. However, this was getting a little bit dicey with readability. While I made sure the colour combinations had a contrast that was &lt;em&gt;technically&lt;/em&gt; accessible, I‚Äôd often go back to a post a few days later and shudder at my appalling colour choices. I needed to ease off the colour and go a little bit cleaner. However, I had picked a colour palette for every page, post and project on my site &lt;em&gt;ever&lt;/em&gt; when I‚Äôd &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/really-a-redesign-this-cant-be-real/&#34; title=&#34;Really, a redesign? This can‚Äôt be real‚Ä¶&#34;&gt;redesigned in 2012&lt;/a&gt;. It‚Äôd be a shame to waste all that effort. I decided to just switch some of the colour palette choices around, so the background was a simpler easy-on-the-eyes grey, and the text would take on the colour. Suddenly the site felt a lot less oppressive!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I learned a lesson in semantic naming that day. Unfortunately, if you rename a field in Advanced Custom Fields, it wipes out the entries in the database for that field, so I‚Äôm stuck with my original palette names such as ‚Äúheader colour‚Äù for the colour of the text. Hopefully the colours match up fairly well, as the contrast hasn‚Äôt changed much, but please let me know if you find a page that‚Äôs hard to read.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;othertweaks&#34;&gt;Other¬†tweaks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of other little fixes and changes I‚Äôve made after having them on my list for ages. Fixing block quote styles, footer layout on certain viewport widths, mismatch of font sizes before and after web font loading, dodgy search box layout and ensuring I‚Äôm not loading the web font loader from Google anymore.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;ssl-hoorah&#34;&gt;SSL hoorah!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And the final thing is that this site now works at &lt;strong&gt;https&lt;/strong&gt;://laurakalbag.wpengine.com.¬†That‚Äôs thanks to WP Engine for enabling SSL as an option on their personal accounts, making it as easy as me pressing a button and paying a little bit of money.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hopefully this site is now a little easier to read, and way more up-to-date. I like to think it‚Äôs a little bit more grown-up. Any further suggestions always gratefully received!&lt;/p&gt;
