&lt;p&gt;The reason I fell in love with the web was the democratisation of information. I love that so many people can access, learn, and share such a huge variety of resources. That‚Äôs why I‚Äôve always considered accessibility so important. To me, access for all¬†is¬†an &lt;em&gt;essential&lt;/em&gt; part of the nature of the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-i-learned-accessibility&#34;&gt;How I learned accessibility&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When I started to learn about web design and development, I learned from great books like &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1430219203/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl&#34;&gt;Dan Cederholm‚Äôs Web Standards Solutions&lt;/a&gt;. Web Standards Solutions continually referred back to why the different markup solutions suggested would be better or worse for accessibility. That‚Äôs how I learned that accessibility was important, part of a developer‚Äôs everyday work and not so hard to achieve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;modern-web-development-and-accessibility&#34;&gt;Modern web development and accessibility&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;nowadays-when-developers-talk-about-modern-web-development-techniques-they-most-often-mention-the-impact-theymay-have-on-web-performance-considering-performance-during-each-step-of-a-project-makes-sense-as-bandwidth-and-battery-life-are-uncertain-commodities-howeverid-really-like-the-community-to-start-talking-again-about-accessibility-in-the-same-way-they-talk-about-web-performance-we-need-tochange-the-minds-of-people-who-think-that-accessibility-doesnt-make-business-sense-and-i-want-the-web-to-be-a-better-place-to-visit-for-a-wider-range-of-people&#34;&gt;Nowadays when developers talk about modern web development techniques, they most often mention the impact they¬†may have on web performance. Considering performance during each step of a project makes sense as bandwidth and battery life are uncertain commodities. However,¬†I‚Äôd really like the community to start talking (again) about accessibility in the same way they talk about web performance. We need to¬†change the minds of people who think that accessibility doesn‚Äôt make business sense, and I want the web to be a better place to visit for a wider range of people.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve written this little post as part of &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.globalaccessibilityawarenessday.org&#34;&gt;Global Accessibility Awareness Day&lt;/a&gt; (#GAAD). Thanks to Neil Milliken and his &lt;a href=&#34;http://atrophiedmind.wordpress.com/2014/05/15/design-choice-is-more-than-just-about-taste-its-an-accessibility-issue/&#34;&gt;fantastic post on designing for accessibility&lt;/a&gt; for the heads-up. If you want to find out more about accessibility, there‚Äôs a &lt;a href=&#34;http://inclusivedesign24.org&#34;&gt;24 hour Inclusive Design community conference&lt;/a&gt; happening online right now (Thanks to &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/brucel&#34;&gt;Bruce Lawson&lt;/a&gt; for tweeting so much about it!)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I also run a Twitter account that shares all the best accessibility resources that I find, it‚Äôs called &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/newtoa11y&#34;&gt;@newtoa11y&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/why-accessibility-matters-to-me-#gaad/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòWhy accessibility matters to me #GAAD‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A couple of months ago, Ian from logogeek.co.uk, asked if I‚Äôd share some of my sketchbook pages on his site. Ian wanted to emphasise the rough, imperfect nature of the way we plan logo designs, and show real work done by real people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last week, Ian added some pages from my sketchbook to &lt;a href=&#34;http://learnlogodesign.com/logo-design-process/a-look-inside-a-designers-sketchbook&#34;&gt;his post, ‚ÄúA look inside a designers sketchbook‚Äù&lt;/a&gt;. He included some of my sketches from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/project/indiephone-logo/&#34; title=&#34;IndiePhone logo&#34;&gt;Indie Phone&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/project/turbine-logo/&#34; title=&#34;Turbine logo&#34;&gt;Turbine&lt;/a&gt; projects. As he didn‚Äôt include all of them, I thought I‚Äôd share them all below.&lt;/p&gt;

