&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/a-little-realign/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòA little realign‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On Friday I was a guest on the &lt;a href=&#34;http://unfinished.bz/64&#34;&gt;Unfinished Business podcast&lt;/a&gt; again. It was a special episode as &lt;a href=&#34;http://rachelandrew.co.uk&#34;&gt;Rachel Andrew&lt;/a&gt; was also a guest (yeah, I designed her site!) I don‚Äôt like to go on about stuff like this too often, but if you‚Äôd told 21 year old me (7 years ago) that I‚Äôd be appearing on a podcast with Andy Clarke and Rachel Andrew, it would‚Äôve blown my mind. They‚Äôre two very lovely people whose writing helped me learn about, and become so excited about, the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The show is focused around the closure of Five Simple Steps, the great publishers of web-themed books, last week. I‚Äôve never written a book, and have only recently started writing much, so I learned a lot from Andy and Rachel as seasoned writers (and ex-Five Simple Steps authors).&lt;/p&gt;
