&lt;p&gt;Here‚Äôs a slightly scary thing: I‚Äôm doing &lt;a href=&#34;http://makedo.in/design-theory-for-the-web/&#34;&gt;my first solo workshop on the 11th October 2013 in Barnsley&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I often get asked about the best way to ‚Äúlearn design‚Äù, and I usually say that you learn by doing and you learn by watching how others do it. In this workshop, I want to give new designers, developers, and anybody else wanting to learn how to design for the web, a good foundation with five primers, a bit of doing and a bit of watching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs a low-cost workshop. The early bird tickets are just ¬£125, and the full-price tickets are just ¬£165. Fancy joining me for the day? &lt;a href=&#34;http://makedo.in/design-theory-for-the-web/#nav-register&#34;&gt;Grab a ticket from the makedo site&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


