&lt;p&gt;Usually I wouldn‚Äôt recommend checking out my slides, as they‚Äôre useless without me explaining them, but as this was an online conference and I wanted the slides to be extra clear in case of technical problems, they hopefully read in a fairly easy-to-follow way:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/conferences/#post-3873&#34;&gt;See the Sass for designers slides on my Conferences page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve also made &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/laurakalbag/webtalkdogwalk&#34;&gt;most of the site code (the stuff not covered by other people‚Äôs licenses!) available on GitHub&lt;/a&gt;. I‚Äôve tried to make the commits fit in with the slides as much as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
