&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/web-talk-dog-walk-the-site/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòWeb talk dog walk, the site‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôm speaking as a ‚ÄòBreakout‚Äô speaker at &lt;a href=&#34;http://2013.dareconf.com/&#34;&gt;Dare conference in September&lt;/a&gt;. As soon as I saw the rumblings of this conference, I knew it was an event I wanted to attend. It‚Äôs focusing on risk, vulnerability, communication and trying to make the world a better place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I realised that I actually had an idea for a talk that could work for this event. I‚Äôd wanted to talk about my openness and honesty online, and how it affects my business. I was only just becoming aware of what I was doing, and writing a talk was a good way for me to dig a little bit deeper. So I wrote a proposal and my proposal was accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The talk has a slightly cheesy name, ‚ÄúMy secret is honesty‚Äù but I promise you, the content is real. I‚Äôve already tested it on a lovely group of people in Porto, Portugal, and hope to have a shortened version ready in September. It‚Äôs a very different topic for me, I usually talk about web design and development, but I think it‚Äôs the right place for an open talk about openness.&lt;/p&gt;


