&lt;h3 id=&#34;20-mockup-fonts-a-month&#34;&gt;20 mockup fonts a month&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This sounds like a very reasonable amount. Am I likely to use more than 20 different fonts over all my mockups in a month? Maybe only just‚Ä¶ Say five family weights (bear in mind, I‚Äôm mocking up, not embedding these all on the web!) on four different projects. That‚Äôs doable. But if you hover over the details of the plan, you see this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mockup fonts are desktop versions of your Web fonts provided exclusively for creating website mockups. Delivered through¬†SkyFonts, mockup fonts remain active for 1 day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Mockup fonts remain active for 1 day.¬†**This means that if I want to use the same font two days running, I use two of my allowed fonts. This means working on a mockup for three days with four fonts, I‚Äôve nearly burned through my allowance already.&lt;/p&gt;


