&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-next-plan-up-allows-unlimited-mockup-fonts-but-costs-nearly-three-times-as-much&#34;&gt;The next plan up allows unlimited mockup fonts but costs nearly three times as much&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As much as I‚Äôd like to upgrade just for the unlimited mockup fonts, I can‚Äôt justify that cost when I won‚Äôt use any of the other features.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;please-fontscom-may-we-have-more-mockup-fonts&#34;&gt;Please fonts.com, may we have more mockup fonts?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For those of use who are small (me, just a one person!) web-based studios, it would be great to have more mockup fonts. We‚Äôre the people who try out your fonts, and then get our clients to subscribe and buy your fonts. We‚Äôre like an extension of your sales team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;ill-happily-pay-slightly-extra-just-not-three-times-the-amount&#34;&gt;I‚Äôll happily pay slightly extra, just not three times the amount&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don‚Äôt doubt the value of the fonts, and I‚Äôm willing to spend money to get quality. Seeing as SkyFonts is doing a good job of allowing rentals, without any concern for piracy, couldn‚Äôt we have more fonts? (Maybe 150 √ó¬†24 hour uses a month?)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I know this is an odd blog post, and probably a niche request. I was going to tweet about it, but realised I just have too much to say in a short post. If anyone else has this problem, please leave a comment!&lt;/p&gt;
