&lt;h2 id=&#34;anyone-can-join-us&#34;&gt;Anyone can join us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No need to bring a dog if you just want to walk and talk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;But please bring a dog or few if you‚Äôve got them, walking with a pack makes it more fun!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don‚Äôt have to be a freelancer or professional or even work with the web, just happy to chat&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don‚Äôt have to come every time, just whenever you fancy it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We‚Äôll leave pretty soon after 9am so please be on time or be willing to catch us up!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don‚Äôt need to let me know beforehand if you‚Äôre coming along, but I‚Äôll know to wait for you if you send me a¬†&lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/laurakalbag&#34;&gt;tweet @laurakalbag&lt;/a&gt;¬†beforehand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wear sensible walking shoes. Trainers should do. It‚Äôs a fairly mud-free route, but it can be rough terrain and a bit hilly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do I need to recommend you wear a jacket if the weather‚Äôs grey? Does it ever rain in Britain?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



