			&lt;img alt=&#39;&#39; src=&#39;https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f9ad38063f9d406b91efb89ea055f75e?s=72&amp;amp;d=mm&amp;amp;r=g&#39; srcset=&#39;https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f9ad38063f9d406b91efb89ea055f75e?s=144&amp;amp;d=mm&amp;amp;r=g 2x&#39; class=&#39;avatar avatar-72 photo&#39; height=&#39;72&#39; width=&#39;72&#39; /&gt;&lt;cite class=&#34;fn&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#39;http://mmandbstudio.co.uk&#39; rel=&#39;external nofollow&#39; class=&#39;url&#39;&gt;Simon Mason&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/cite&gt;
				&lt;aside class=&#34;comment-meta commentmetadata&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#comment-550&#34;&gt;&lt;time datetime=&#34;2013-06-11T15:01:04+00:00&#34; pubdate class=&#34;published&#34;&gt;
		 at &lt;span class=&#34;hours&#34;&gt;15:01pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/aside&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		I get more irritated by the fact Apple‚Äôs website still isn‚Äôt responsive, because, you know pinch and zoom is all you need &amp;#8230;
&lt;p&gt;Anyway come October there will no doubt be lots of praise for the new iOS7 shiny.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Funny how people love the new but hate change.&lt;/p&gt;
