&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôm really looking forward to October, where I get to return to Portugal to speak at &lt;a href=&#34;http://2013.lxjs.org/&#34;&gt;LXJS in Lisbon&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the reasons I jumped at the chance to speak at LXJS was their fantastic &lt;a href=&#34;http://2013.lxjs.org/code-of-conduct&#34;&gt;Code of Conduct&lt;/a&gt;. After &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jenseninman.com/blog/13737040/speakingupitstime&#34;&gt;hearing some&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.sazzy.co.uk/2013/02/speaking-up/&#34;&gt;horror stories&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.sazzy.co.uk/2013/02/speaking-up/&#34;&gt;from other women speakers&lt;/a&gt;, I wish more conferences had this sort of approach. It‚Äôs friendly, not strict, and lets everybody know where they stand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The tickets are incredibly reasonable for a two-day event, and it looks like Lisbon is well-worth a holiday so a conference there is a bonus!&lt;/p&gt;


