		It‚Äôs so difficult to comment on this one&amp;#8230; Kudos for having the strength to admit if though, I know what it feels to go through all this, and the hardest part is probably to admit it publicly.
&lt;p&gt;One deep cause that I‚Äôve been able to identify was lacking a reason to keep on with the daily work routine that was progressively burning me out. After a year or so since I‚Äôve finally realized this, I‚Äôve still to figure out what could possibly change my mind so deeply (hint : at least I know it includes life changing decisions both in my work and in my personal life‚Ä¶)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reading Peter Bregman‚Äôs 18 Minutes has helped me a lot figuring out all this&amp;#8230; If you haven‚Äôt read it yet, it‚Äôs worth giving it a try.
