  &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-solution&#34;&gt;The solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I knew Mail.app wasn‚Äôt hugely customisable, but I thought I could try using &lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emoji&#34;&gt;emoji characters&lt;/a&gt;¬†in the names of the smart mailboxes as you can have coloured characters, rather than the one-colour characters in most fonts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;getting-emoji&#34;&gt;Getting Emoji&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After some quick web searches, I couldn‚Äôt find any sites or apps that allowed me to grab the emoji I wanted. So I just wrote myself an iMessage with the emoji characters I thought might worked and send it to myself. With iMessage‚Äôs unreliability, I didn‚Äôt get it for ages, so in the meantime I copied and pasted the emoji into an email and sent it to myself.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;figure&gt;


    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;771&#39; height=&#39;173&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/using-emoji-in-mail.app-to-make-better-visual-indicators/Screen-Shot-2013-02-10-at-15.16.35_hu910d90b8bf65d25371a6b01468f9a1bd_19348_300x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 300w,/using-emoji-in-mail.app-to-make-better-visual-indicators/Screen-Shot-2013-02-10-at-15.16.35_hu910d90b8bf65d25371a6b01468f9a1bd_19348_500x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 500w,/using-emoji-in-mail.app-to-make-better-visual-indicators/Screen-Shot-2013-02-10-at-15.16.35.png 771w&#39;
