&lt;p&gt;Yesterday I was a guest on &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/ttimsmith&#34;&gt;Tim Smith&lt;/a&gt;‚Äòs &lt;a href=&#34;http://theeastwing.net/&#34;&gt;The East Wing podcast&lt;/a&gt;. It was a pre-recorded conversation and it was great fun. You can &lt;a href=&#34;http://theeastwing.net/episodes/laura-kalbag&#34;&gt;listen to it on the East Wing website&lt;/a&gt;, and it‚Äôll be up on iTunes soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We discussed how I got started in the industry (really sorry traditional Graphic Design people, I may have generalised a bit‚Ä¶), speaking at conferences, women in the industry and mentoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/laurakalbag/status/298862630506991616&#34;&gt;I said last night on Twitter&lt;/a&gt;,¬†Tim Smith is such a great guy. I really had my heart warmed and faith in humanity boosted by our conversation. His thoughts on women in the industry made me proud to be part of the web community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And if you don‚Äôt already &lt;a href=&#34;https://itunes.apple.com/gb/podcast/the-east-wing/id503801143?mt=2&#34;&gt;subscribe to The East Wing podcast&lt;/a&gt;, do it! It‚Äôs full of great, and inspiring, insight on the people behind the work in the web industry.&lt;/p&gt;



