		I really like this article much. You mention the most valid points and problems we currently have (won‚Äôt limit that to our industry as this appears in many more industries the same way).
&lt;p&gt;Just to add one thing to your personal experience: I am sorry about this, this tweet is unnecessary. But as a male (it just doesn‚Äôt matter I want to say with that) speaker who is not known very much and new to speaking you get such comments regardless of your gender. I also got some very disappointing comments on some talks of me. I do think this is very unpleasant to people who speak because they want to share something. People are taking ones self-confidence with such statements.
&lt;p&gt;Spoken for most speakers (I am assuming here) I don‚Äôt think they want to be speakers because they wanna be rock-stars but because they want to share something. Criticize them by just tweeting / writing such crappy statements just shows how poor-minded the person is who writes or says this.&lt;/p&gt;
