	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		Thank you, you lot :)
&lt;p&gt;@Mark It‚Äôs not that I find more kinship with women, I just find them particularly inspiring in this way. That‚Äôs why I tried to emphasise at the beginning that they certainly aren‚Äôt my only inspiration. And why I mentioned that those who support these people are equally included.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are so many people I love and respect, and I‚Äôm sure that most of them are men, because there are just so many more men in the industry. It‚Äôs this difficulty of being one type of minority that makes it so easy to feel slighted or disheartened, and those who get past that are often under-appreciated or suffer extra scrutiny for their trouble. It‚Äôs also so important to for these groups of people to have people they can look up to and take assurance from. Of course, they don‚Äôt have to be the same minority, but sometimes it just helps.
&lt;/div&gt;
