&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/grid-frameworks-and-why-im-not-keen-on-them/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòGrid Frameworks and why I‚Äôm not keen on them‚Ä¶‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2012 has been a massive year for me. It was a year of saying yes to things that scared me. It was the first time I spoke at a conference (and &lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/conferences/&#34; title=&#34;Conferences&#34;&gt;I went on to speak at a further seven events.&lt;/a&gt;) I found the first house I‚Äôve lived in by myself. I travelled to as many countries in one year as I had done in my whole life so far. It was the end of a long relationship and a completely unexpected falling head-over-heels into a new one. And I got this tiny little puppy who didn‚Äôt just become enormous, but became one of the biggest and best things in my life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I started writing a long post detailing each month and realised I have too many highlights and I‚Äôd be here all night. However this year was the year I started taking lots of photos. So I thought I‚Äôd share the few that mean the most to me.&lt;/p&gt;

