	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Hey Laura,
&lt;p&gt;Don‚Äôt beat yourself up. I think it is also important to realise that everybody is in the same 140char limit as you, and many can (and do) read between the lines. I saw your tweet and wrongly or rightly put 2+2 together, and drew my own conclusion, as I‚Äôm sure other people will have. My personal opinion is that frameworks are fantastic for quick prototypes and putting ideas together, but I still prefer to start with a blank template when it comes down to it‚Ä¶. so yes, those few characters you wrote will always say something different to the reader, wrong or right.&lt;/p&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
