	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your encouragement.
&lt;p&gt;Hiding images by display none is a big issue, because they load anyway. The following research breaks the ice by documenting that ‚Äúbackground images attached to elements that are inside a element with display none are NOT loaded‚Äù: [http://timkadlec.com/2012/04/media-query-asset-downloading-results](&lt;a href=&#34;http://timkadlec.com/2012/04/media-query-asset-downloading-results%22&#34;&gt;http://timkadlec.com/2012/04/media-query-asset-downloading-results&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt; rel=&amp;ldquo;nofollow)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Loading images with a common 1x1px src (because the attribute cannot be empty) AND inline styling its background-image to the ‚Äòoriginal‚Äô src you are able to control the load by conditionally replacing the src with the background-image src ‚Äì and showing the parent element. Only then will the image load.&lt;/p&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
