	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		Very familiar with this issue as I‚Äôve strived to do RWD without having to customise much of the server-side or the JS. And doing so means display: none; is almost a necessity.
&lt;p&gt;In an upcoming iteration, I‚Äôve resorted to using more Ajax requests with checks for the user-agent. It‚Äôs arguably more naughty than just ‚Äúdisplay: none;‚Äù, because now there‚Äôs a bit of JS coupled to the stylesheet, but since it improves performance, it‚Äôs a net gain.
