&lt;li&gt;**&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.potionfactory.com/thehitlist/&#34;&gt;The Hit List&lt;/a&gt;.¬†**The best to-do list app I‚Äôve used. It‚Äôs quick to open and has some of the best keyboard shortcuts ever to make it really quick to use. I‚Äôve never managed to get the syncing with the iPhone app working quite right though‚Ä¶&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://reederapp.com/&#34;&gt;Reeder&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; Nice app for reading your RSS feeds. I think my Reeder might be a bit dusty, as I don‚Äôt often get time to read my feeds, but it sits in my dock reminding me that I should catch up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/browser/&#34;&gt;Google Chrome&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; The browser I wish I didn‚Äôt have to use but do. It has the best developer tools asides from Firefox‚Ä¶&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/&#34;&gt;Firefox&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; I really really want to use Firefox as my main browser but it‚Äôs so sluggish I think it gives Photoshop competition. In the dock for cross-browser testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.opera.com/&#34;&gt;Opera&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; For cross-browser testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.apple.com/safari/&#34;&gt;Safari&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;Mac OSX default&lt;/em&gt;)¬†For cross-browser testing.&lt;/li&gt;
