Thanks for this insightful article, it‚Äôs always good to see how other approach it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One thing I have noticed recently is that using ‚Äôem‚Äôs for media queries seems to be working a little better than pixel values. You can view what happens when you zoom in to the page with the browser (CTRL + usually) and see that the media query ‚Äòbreaks‚Äô. By using ‚Äôem‚Äôs, which are relative, they will keep working, which is great if content should decide the breakpoints and you value your users settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My 2 cents on this subject!
