There was too much I wanted to change. The way I‚Äôd configured WordPress before was quite awkward to maintain (there was a lot of HTML required when adding new projects) and I wanted to make use of the newer CMS-like features that WordPress offered (like custom post types and custom taxonomies.) Also, when designing a responsive site, it‚Äôs much cleaner to rewrite from mobile CSS first which would have meant refactoring &lt;strong&gt;all&lt;/strong&gt; the markup!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And then there‚Äôs the fact that I was just sick of the old design. I know this one isn‚Äôt exactly ‚Äòmodern‚Äô, but the old version was definitely ‚Äòold school‚Äô‚Ä¶ ;)
