&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôd say that the Fitbit is really best if you‚Äôre a walker or a runner, as it really is just a pedometer. You can easily record other types of exercise through their Activity Log but these are just basing a lot of the values on averages, rather than the actual calories you are likely to have burnt, actual steps taken etc. This doesn‚Äôt mean that the Fitbit is useless though. The majority of exercise I do (asides from walking) isn‚Äôt something that the Fitbit records itself, activities like biking or lifting weights. It will pick up that you‚Äôre doing some kind of activity, but won‚Äôt necessarily reflect the intensity. I actually find this just pushes me harder to do more exercise that the Fitbit &lt;strong&gt;does&lt;/strong&gt; record.&lt;/p&gt;



