	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		It‚Äôs something I do with ads ([http://www.welcomebrand.co.uk/thoughts/browsing-an-uglier-web-on-purpose/](http://www.welcomebrand.co.uk/thoughts/browsing-an-uglier-web-on-purpose/&#34; rel=&#34;nofollow)) and I do recommend everyone do it from time to time for the reasons you mention. 
&lt;p&gt;As designers, we‚Äôre a million miles away from how many ‚Äúaverage‚Äù users operate on the net and if you work on any sort of larger scale projects and get the change to watch video tests of users it‚Äôll open your eyes just how differently they use the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs also worth reminding mac toting designers everywhere to check what their work looks like on a windows machine, you‚Äôd be amazed how many sites (designers portfolios in particular) I see on daily basis that are unreadable due to the differences in font rendering etc.&lt;/p&gt;
