&lt;p&gt;There‚Äôs something that‚Äôs been bothering me lately. It seems to be some kind of form interface trend where the labels for text inputs are placed inside the fields themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;226&#39; height=&#39;54&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/labels-in-input-fields-arent-such-a-good-idea/Screen-shot-2011-05-27-at-16.48.49.png 226w&#39;
      src=&#39;Screen-shot-2011-05-27-at-16.48.49.png&#39; alt=&#39;a form field where the label is shown inside the text input field&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;there-might-be-some-pros&#34;&gt;There might be some pros&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Admittedly, this makes an interface slicker. It saves space where you‚Äôd usually have a label, then some padding, then the input field and probably a load of padding around the lot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But what you‚Äôre gaining in a clean look, you‚Äôre completely losing through a total lack of usability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;so-im-an-interface-idiot&#34;&gt;So, I‚Äôm an interface idiot&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You know the lowest common denominator, idiot users that we design easy interfaces for? The ones that need to be led by the hand, step by step, across your design to get to the call-to-action?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That‚Äôs me, that is. I am an incredibly na√Øve user. I skim read, I‚Äôm forgetful, I barely pay attention and when I do I‚Äôm easily confused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;this-is-what-i-see&#34;&gt;This is what I see&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here‚Äôs an example from a site that is otherwise a shimmering beacon of awesomeness over the wasteland that is the web:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;project-noah&#34;&gt;Project Noah&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of Project Noah, you upload photos of nature. The aim is to identify the creature or plant in your photo, and part of that is providing the relevant links to that species‚Äô page on Wikipedia and the Encyclopedia of Life.&lt;/p&gt;
