&lt;p&gt;Probably most importantly, the squares are more subtle. Moleskine squares are bold and black and you notice their presence. With the¬†Leuchtturm1917, the squares are so subtle that once you‚Äôve used a page, you barely notice them behind the contrast of ink pen. This would make it much better for pencil drawings as they‚Äôd definitely be harder to see on the Moleskine counterpart.&lt;/p&gt;

