&lt;p&gt;First off, let me declare my complete bias. I‚Äôve been involved with the Big M conference from pretty early on, I was lucky enough to do all the design work and the organisers are lovely guys who I‚Äôm proud to call my friends. I‚Äôm still on a high from how much I enjoyed myself (and just about recovered from the surreal feeling of being in a place with my own design work &lt;em&gt;everywhere&lt;/em&gt;) so this is really going to be the most biased event review you‚Äôve ever read!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-attendees&#34;&gt;The Attendees&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It was a complete mixture of attendees, ranging from business entrepreneurs to freelancers, mobile operators to web developers and UX experts. What really stuck out was that everybody seemed friendly, enthusiastic and engaged in the day. I didn‚Äôt spot any boring/bored looking ‚Äòsuits‚Äô and it made for a fun atmosphere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-venue&#34;&gt;The Venue&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great point made in &lt;a href=&#34;http://adambird.com/the-big-m-went-bold-and-got-it-so-right&#34; title=&#34;Adam Bird&#39;s review of The Big M&#34;&gt;Adam Bird‚Äôs review&lt;/a&gt; was that Komedia in Bath made for a great conference day venue as it usually hosts comedy and music events. Such a good point. The venue being a slightly dark and very colourful room made for a relaxed and informal feel to the conference. It was the right size for about 200 people so it didn‚Äôt feel over-crowded or empty at any point. The chairs were a bit hard, but I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve ever been to an event where that wasn‚Äôt a problem‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-speakers&#34;&gt;The Speakers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a designer, and a previous attendee of the &lt;a href=&#34;http://open-mic.org.uk/&#34; title=&#34;openMIC mobile innovation events&#34;&gt;openMIC events&lt;/a&gt;, I usually expect most of the talks to go over my head. I‚Äôm not a big business brain, never really worked in the mobile industry and mobile development is a lot more complicated than the majority of web markup/frontend development that I do. However, this wasn‚Äôt the case at all at The Big M.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The speakers were all experienced presenters. Often you‚Äôll find one ‚Äòdud‚Äô talk at a conference, but there wasn‚Äôt one here. Whilst some of the speakers presented on more controversial topics that I wouldn‚Äôt necessarily agree on, each made their points well, engaging the audience and inspiring loads of discussion in the Q and As and breaks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here‚Äôs a brief rundown of some of the main points (and some of my terrible iPhone photos) I tweeted from the talks as well as some brilliant tweets from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf&#34;&gt;@bigmconf&lt;/a&gt; where all the talks were live-tweeted:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;raam-thakrar-app-distribution-and-monetisation--the-only-things-more-important-than-lines-of-code&#34;&gt;Raam Thakrar ‚Äì;¬†App distribution and monetisation ‚Äì; the only things more important than lines of code&lt;/h3&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;portrait&#39;
      width=&#39;476&#39; height=&#39;640&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/the-big-m/IMG_0537_hue74960c90c2e0d4405483f2a5085000f_81089_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/the-big-m/IMG_0537.jpg 476w&#39;
      src=&#39;IMG_0537.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;Raam Thakrar&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thakrar: We need to think about why a consumer buys a phone, what part we play in the decision &amp;amp; how can we monetise this &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf/status/49767361464647680&#34;&gt;From @bigmconf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;software and apps are now a deciding factor when people are buying handsets, so app devs should use this to work with operators&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thakrar: Specific lessons: develop an app that consumers love and thus influences their choice about what they do with their money &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf/status/497710145524326400&#34;&gt;From @bigmconf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
