&lt;p&gt;Openness is about giving developers choice so they can come to one platform and create content they can use on other platforms &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf/status/49810212210737153&#34;&gt;From @bigmconf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Openness: At some point you are going to die and your work is going to live on, but the only way it can do that is to be locked in &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf/status/49811351819923456&#34;&gt;From @bigmconf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Openness often hits the barriers of brand protection and content protection &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bigmconf/status/49814525934968832&#34;&gt;From @bigmconf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
