	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		This web celebrity thing is getting out of hand. I find it implausible people are referring to themselves as rock stars and ninjas when we&amp;#039;re essentially a service industry.
&lt;p&gt;I donÔøΩt see plumbers putting each other on a pedestal, or stepping out and calling themselves rock stars, ninjas and the like. I donÔøΩt see mechanics putting together Top Trumps-style cards (any one remember Type Faces?).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ItÔøΩs all, for want of a better term, a load of bollocks. I joined Dribbble earlier this year, and as soon as the novelty wore off grew dissatisfied with it. ThereÔøΩs no community feel to the website, but more so establishing trends and a breeding ground for iTunes 10 replacement logos, or GAP replacement logos, or whatever will come along next week that the community at large decide isnÔøΩt worthy.
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
