&lt;p&gt;hehehe!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IÔøΩm a bit torn about the whole situation, but, at the same time, thereÔøΩs still a lot of rubbish designers on dribbble anyway (sorry, let me rephrase that as designers who are first starting out who need a lot of help to improve), and while IÔøΩm not a regular user the system, I think itÔøΩs good to have a place to show things off to your peers.  Snobbery in design is not a new thing (I hung out with some architects recently and oh do they think web design is not a very noble profession!), and while you can claim you donÔøΩt like it, youÔøΩre not going to stop it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When IÔøΩm excited about something cool IÔøΩve done, whatÔøΩs wrong with showing it to the type of people who might give you compliments?
