	&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
		The beauty and uniqueness of Dribbble is exactly in the fact that it is a hand-picked and a &amp;#039;gated&amp;#039; community. Aren&amp;#039;t there a lot of different places that are open for all, like DeviantArt.
&lt;p&gt;While elitism sounds like a curse word it can be beneficial like I think it is in this case, we could also call it with a name that I find more appropriate in this case ‚Äì; &lt;b&gt;peer review&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Snobbery is a sad and stupid trait and should be (IMHO) ignored when it springs up, but letÔøΩs not associate it directly with peer review.
