&lt;p&gt;I posted as much identical information as I could to both Dribbble and Forrst. Generally, I could include a larger, more detailed image on Forrst as there‚Äôs no size limitation. I also posted more frequently to Forrst as it has no limit on posts, whereas Dribbble limits the amount of posts over a month (usually around twenty if you use them all.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-stats&#34;&gt;The Stats&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;forrst&#34;&gt;Forrst&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Posts ‚Äì; 12&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Views ‚Äì; 80*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Likes ‚Äì; 34&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comments ‚Äì; 13&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** I get the feeling this stat might be wrong, as on some posts I have more likes than views.*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;dribbble&#34;&gt;Dribbble&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Posts ‚Äì; 7&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Views ‚Äì; 842&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Likes ‚Äì; 14&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comments ‚Äì; 16&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you can see, the Dribbblers seemed more likely to give their opinion, but much less likely to ‚Äòlike‚Äô the post!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-dribbble-and-forrst-feedback-helped&#34;&gt;How Dribbble and Forrst feedback helped&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Overall, there was a lot of approval and a positive reaction to my design. This was great as it made me feel as though I was heading in the right direction, and let Andy know that potential users of the site were keen on the logo.&lt;/p&gt;



