&lt;div class=&#34;comment-entry&#34;&gt;
If itÔøΩs ÔøΩweÔøΩ doing the work then ÔøΩweÔøΩ should get the credit, it would be wrong to claim that ÔøΩmeÔøΩ is doing the work when itÔøΩs really more than one person. IÔøΩd be pretty annoyed if I hired someone to do work for me and found out that theyÔøΩd outsourced it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I just think that everybody should make it perfectly clear who is doing what in those cases. You donÔøΩt have to confuse a client with the technicalities, but thereÔøΩs no harm in saying ÔøΩI donÔøΩt do this, but so-and-so does so I pay them to do it for me. Is that cool with you?ÔøΩ
&lt;/div&gt;
