1) I want to get bigger clients, and like it or not, they won‚Äôt use individuals for big complex projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nonsense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TheyÔøΩll use an individual.  ItÔøΩs all in your head.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You donÔøΩt believe theyÔøΩd want you .. and so you probably never asked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ItÔøΩs like saying &amp;quot;that stunning girl would never go our with an bloke like me.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actually, she probably would.  IÔøΩve seen stunning girls with ugly blokes (that arenÔøΩt rich) .. itÔøΩs probably at least partly down to the fact the ugly bloke sheÔøΩs with actually asked her out .. and partly down to the confidence he had.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ItÔøΩs the same with a big company.  If you donÔøΩt ask them .. or you donÔøΩt put across the plus points of being an individual, sure they wonÔøΩt hire you.  But thatÔøΩs your fault for not selling yourself well enough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plus points of being an individual:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äì; youÔøΩre a big client to me.  Not like some big ad agency where youÔøΩre just another number to invoice.  IÔøΩll pull out all the stops for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äì; IÔøΩm cheaper, because I have lower overheads&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äì; You spend less money and get a better developer to boot!  An ad agency charges you ¬£100/hr and in return you get a ¬£10/hr developer. The rest goes on overheads and profit.  I charge you ¬£35/hr and you get a ¬£35/hr developer.  My overheads are lower, and IÔøΩm not passing the work on to some junior whoÔøΩs not that good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚Äì; I donÔøΩt mean to be rude, but IÔøΩm better than the agency.  They canÔøΩt afford me ‚Äì; thatÔøΩs why IÔøΩm freelance.  They have to hire somebody cheaper.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Etc etc etc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As for the &amp;quot;for complex projects&amp;quot; bit.  You shouldnÔøΩt take on projects that are too complex for you anyway, so if thatÔøΩs an issue youÔøΩre pitching for the wrong work.
&lt;/div&gt;
