2) I intend to outsource the development side going forward as it‚Äôs the part I‚Äôm less good at and don‚Äôt enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I do the design.  And when I feel like it, I do the coding too.  But sometimes, I get someone else to do that stuff.  It means I can concentrate on the bits I‚Äôm good and it means I can make sure I don‚Äôt miss the deadlines I‚Äôve agree with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That means you‚Äôre happy and I am happy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I‚Äôm considering offering hosting to future clients (I currently don‚Äôt) ‚Äî and the hosting company offer free white label support to my clients, so they would appear to be my employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I offer hosting to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I use a company which can offer you extra support on your hosting, so if you ever have a problem they can help you fix it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That‚Äôs better for you, because it means you can phone them out of hours and ‚Äì; to be honest ‚Äì; they deal with hosting all day long so know much more about it than me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚ÄúWe‚Äù gives you the scope to expand in the future. ‚ÄúI‚Äù doesn‚Äôt. I don‚Äôt want to be seen as some cheap freelancer when I‚Äôm 50 (assuming I‚Äôm still doing this!) ‚Äî I want to be seen as a respectable provider and however you cut it, ‚ÄúI‚Äù just doesn‚Äôt have the same weight in that regard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OK, I think I‚Äôve already said where I stand on ‚ÄúI‚Äù vs ‚Äúwe‚Äù in terms of credibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you decide to expand, start off by saying ‚ÄúI‚Äôve just take on a guy called Paul (it should always be a Paul BTW!) to help me out with some of the coding work.‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then, at some stage, once that‚Äôs been going on for a while and you decide to take on another person then you can move to being ‚Äúwe‚Äù.  Then it‚Äôll be genuine, and will make you and your clients much happier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 point ‚Äì; make sure once you start trading as ‚Äúwe‚Äù that you don‚Äôt use your own name.  Don‚Äôt be Matt Hill Design.  Be Hillybilly Design, or something.  It‚Äôll make it clear to your clients that it‚Äôs now a company, not just one person.
