&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laurakalbag.com/me-vs-we/&#34;&gt;Read the original post, ‚ÄòMe vs We‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs been a whole year since I officially started working as a freelance designer last August.¬†I graduated from uni, had a brief fling with some full-time remote working, had an awkward interview with a recruiter and then decided that I‚Äôd rather give it a go by myself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;getting-started&#34;&gt;Getting Started&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I felt pretty ready for freelancing full-time, I‚Äôd had a lot of experience on projects whilst I was at university. I knew I could run a project and I knew I could do the work. I‚Äôd done a one-day course at uni in freelance accounting and got myself a business account and subscription to &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.freeagentcentral.com/?referrer=32rbfqy3&#34; title=&#34;FreeAgent freelance accounting software&#34;&gt;FreeAgent&lt;/a&gt; so I felt like I could stay on top of the finance side.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first month started pretty slowly, but that was only the first month. With the help of two lovely people in particular, &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bookmeister&#34; title=&#34;Chris Book on Twitter&#34;&gt;Chris Book&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/simonwheatley&#34; title=&#34;Simon Wheatley on Twitter&#34;&gt;Simon Wheatley&lt;/a&gt;, I got to know a few people and started getting a few projects under my belt. I really couldn‚Äôt thank these two guys enough for recommending me to their friends and giving me great opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôve found that meeting people (I don‚Äôt like &lt;em&gt;networking&lt;/em&gt;, it‚Äôs too false) is incredibly important when you‚Äôre starting out. After that, my network seemed to grow itself!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-stats&#34;&gt;The Stats&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can‚Äôt believe how much I‚Äôve done. I‚Äôve just worked these out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Projects completed ‚Äì; 27&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current projects ‚Äì; 6&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;WordPress themes created ‚Äì; 13&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logos designed ‚Äì; 10&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;iPhone app designs ‚Äì; 3&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Static website designs ‚Äì; 6&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Illustration projects ‚Äì; 2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Website maintenance projects ‚Äì; 3&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HTML e-mail designs ‚Äì; 1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;getting-work&#34;&gt;Getting Work&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the stats above, you can see that I‚Äôve been busy! Thanks to Chris and Simon and a lot of really great clients, I‚Äôve managed to be constantly booked up and busy since last October. I‚Äôm now booking up around two/three months in advance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs been difficult. Learning to not stress and cope with a big workload is one of the many things I‚Äôve tried to get my head around.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;trying-to-learn&#34;&gt;Trying to learn&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not necessarily things I‚Äôve already learnt, but things I‚Äôm in the process of learning!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;scheduling-projects-is-all-well-and-good-but-nothing-ever-stays-on-schedule&#34;&gt;Scheduling projects is all well and good but &lt;strong&gt;nothing&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;ever&lt;/em&gt; stays on schedule.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feedback isn‚Äôt instant, work takes much longer or nowhere near as long as estimated. It‚Äôs not a nightmare if I don‚Äôt stress about it, but I‚Äôm getting good at frequently reorganising and juggling projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;desk-space-is-important&#34;&gt;Desk space is important.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work got miles easier when I had my own working area set up. Matt built me a great custom desk, shelf unit and wall-mounted my second screen. When I‚Äôm at my desk, I‚Äôm working. The division between working at home and just being at home makes a big difference.&lt;/p&gt;

