&lt;p&gt;If you want to try TwentyTen out, you can find it in the &lt;a href=&#34;http://wordpress.org/extend/themes/twentyten&#34;&gt;WordPress theme repository&lt;/a&gt; and through the Themes &amp;gt; ‚ÄòInstall‚Äô section in your WordPress admin by searching ‚Äòtwentyten‚Äô.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;wordpress-admin-realign&#34;&gt;WordPress admin realign&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you follow me on Twitter, you might have heard me whining a bit about the new WordPress admin realign. I‚Äôll call it a realign as they‚Äôve only made some changes, not redesigned the lot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The idea behind these changes is that it brings the content into focus, and it is more legible to read dark text on a light background so it makes the WordPress admin, which is now entirely dark on light, more accessible.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;figure&gt;


    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;935&#39; height=&#39;687&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_300x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 300w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_500x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 500w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_800x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 800w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11.png 935w&#39;
      src=&#39;Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11.png&#39; alt=&#39;WordPress 3.0 admin&#39;
    /&gt;

    &lt;figcaption&gt;


      &lt;p&gt;WordPress 3.0 admin&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have the utmost respect for those working on the WordPress admin interface, and have briefly discussed the decisions with &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/JohnONolan&#34;&gt;John O‚ÄôNolan&lt;/a&gt;, member of the Core WordPress UI Team, on Twitter. I appreciate their reasons behind the changes and that it must be very difficult to please everybody in these scenarios. (Here comes the &lt;em&gt;but&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;But&lt;/strong&gt; I find the new admin harder to use, and I don‚Äôt believe it is out of a lack of familiarity. Here are my reasons:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;there-is-a-general-lack-of-contrast-across-all-the-admin&#34;&gt;There is a general lack of contrast across all the admin&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;935&#39; height=&#39;687&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_300x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 300w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_500x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 500w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11_hu8e0aa5eb758f5e99d2b984d455cf40eb_216592_800x0_resize_mitchellnetravali_2.png 800w,/wordpress-3.0-part-3theme-development-and-the-design/Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11.png 935w&#39;
      src=&#39;Screen-shot-2010-07-16-at-20.48.11.png&#39; alt=&#39;WordPress 3.0 admin&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is all dark grey against white and light grey backgrounds separated by light grey border lines. My eye isn‚Äôt drawn to any different elements anymore, it doesn‚Äôt suggest so strongly where I am or where I should go first. I‚Äôm an idiot and need to be led!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;when-you-select-the-title-text-box-when-creating-a-new-post-the-label-for-the-text-box-disappears&#34;&gt;When you select the title text box when creating a new post, the label for the text box disappears&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

  &lt;figure&gt;


    &lt;img
