&lt;p&gt;If you have cognitive issues, I can‚Äôt see how this is accessible. Chances are, you‚Äôll select that first input box available and then be clueless about what that box is for. The label-in-an-input-box isn‚Äôt yet a strong-enough standard to make it obvious that you need to deselect the text input. It‚Äôs more of a consistent pattern for search input boxes, where the function is made obvious by the accompanying presence of a ‚ÄòSearch‚Äô button.&lt;/p&gt;
