  &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This little alert that lets you know if you have comments, or need to update your plugins or WordPress installation, used to be orange. Orange stood out against the mostly white/grey/blue colour scheme and was clearly there to be noticed. Orange signifies something to be aware about, not quite red being something dangerous but not green for ‚Äòeverything is fine‚Äô. Even though this new alert style is a reversible of the dark-on-light text shown everywhere else, I think it‚Äôs a very unusual choice to have something less colourful for an alert.&lt;/p&gt;
