&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;discography&#34;&gt;Discography&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It‚Äôs pretty self-explanatory, I used the custom post types to list a new CD in each post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;books&#34;&gt;Books&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each one of Stuart‚Äôs books has its own post in the ‚ÄòBooks‚Äô post type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a bit less obvious. In the sidebar or footer on every page is a feature that shows a latest book, video or audio track.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this I used a custom post type of ‚ÄòFeature‚Äô with a featured image to show the image and using the title and text content (even though it‚Äôs very little text) as standard. The ‚ÄòBuy Now‚Äô button is created by entering a URL and button text into a &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.deluxeblogtips.com/2010/04/how-to-create-meta-box-wordpress-post.html&#34;&gt;custom write panel&lt;/a&gt; (also known as &lt;a href=&#34;http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/add_meta_box&#34;&gt;meta boxes&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;gear&#34;&gt;Gear&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The gear is pretty special as I made use of a ‚ÄòGear‚Äô custom post type with a ‚ÄòType of gear‚Äô custom taxonomy. You certainly couldn‚Äôt do that a few versions ago!&lt;/p&gt;

