&lt;h3 id=&#34;loopphp-and-other-template-parts&#34;&gt;loop.php and other Template Parts&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A change in WordPress 3.0 that I‚Äôm a bit confused about is the template parts, which separates the WordPress loop into its own file, loop.php. It is certainly not necessary to do this in order¬†to make your WordPress theme work, and the idea behind doing this is that you can now easily separate repeatable parts of your templates into different files and call them when you need them, thus preventing you repeating yourself many times in one file and needing to edit the same repeated line of code multiple times just because you want to change a few characters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, the implementation of this in the new default TwentyTen theme seems to contradict this non-repetitive, breaking up into digestible chunks, sensibility. Apologies for the huge amount of code that follows:&lt;/p&gt;
