      src=&#39;photo2.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;middle layer on my fish picture&#39;
    /&gt;
Then over the top, I tried to make the detail a bit more subtle and give the fish a slightly more realistic 3D multi-coloured appearance.&lt;/p&gt;



    &lt;img
      class=&#39;landscape&#39;
      width=&#39;1024&#39; height=&#39;768&#39;
      sizes=&#39;(min-width: 1380px) 750px, (min-width: 820px) 719px, (min-width: 740px) calc(-33.33vw &amp;#43; 875px), (min-width: 340px) calc(92.63vw - 39px), calc(100vw - 32px)&#39;
      srcset=&#39;https://laurakalbag.com/autodesk-sketchbook-pro/photo1_hu9822c6e980f431c799d808836d8eca9d_130679_300x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 300w,/autodesk-sketchbook-pro/photo1_hu9822c6e980f431c799d808836d8eca9d_130679_500x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 500w,/autodesk-sketchbook-pro/photo1_hu9822c6e980f431c799d808836d8eca9d_130679_800x0_resize_q80_mitchellnetravali.jpg 800w,/autodesk-sketchbook-pro/photo1.jpg 1024w&#39;
      src=&#39;photo1.jpg&#39; alt=&#39;layers in SketchBook Pro&#39;
    /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôm pretty pleased with the overall effect and I‚Äôll definitely keep trying to practice drawing and sketching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are other features of SketchBook Pro as well! My sister liked the mirrored setting and another friend made a great landscape using textured brushes for plants and flowers. I‚Äôll also be looking out for further Autodesk apps as they seem to have the iPad interface totally nailed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you fancy getting a bit creative on the iPad, &lt;a href=&#34;http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/sketchbook-pro/id364253478?mt=8&#34; title=&#34;SketchBook Pro on iTunes&#34;&gt;go download SketchBook Pro from the App Store&lt;/a&gt;. At ¬£4.99 it‚Äôs a steal. The amount of thought and skill gone into the user experience of the app makes it worth far more, and undoubtably more than many higher-priced apps.&lt;/p&gt;
